high blood pressure?</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>You have <strong>high blood pressure</strong> (medically known as hypertension) if check-ups on separate occasions show your blood pressure to be <strong>140/90mmHg or higher</strong>.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>A blood pressure reading below <strong>130/80mmHg</strong> is considered <strong>normal.</strong></p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>Who is at risk?</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>You are more likely to have high blood pressure as you get older. High blood pressure often has no clear cause, but your risk is higher if you:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>are overweight</li>\r\n	<li>have a relative with high blood pressure</li>\r\n	<li>don&#39;t eat many fruits and vegetables</li>\r\n	<li>don&#39;t take enough exercise</li>\r\n	<li>drink a lot of alcohol</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You can take steps to prevent high blood pressure by:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>losing weight if you need to</li>\r\n	<li>exercising regularly</li>\r\n	<li>eating a healthy diet</li>\r\n	<li>cutting back if you drink a lot of alcohol</li>\r\n	<li>stopping smoking</li>\r\n</ul>', '<h3>Further Supports</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>NHS information on high blood pressure:</p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href="http://www.nhs.uk/conditions/Blood-pressure-(high)/Pages/Introduction.aspx">http://www.nhs.uk/conditions/Blood-pressure-(high)/Pages/Introduction.aspx</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>British Heart Foundation information on blood pressure:</p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href="https://www.bhf.org.uk/heart-health/conditions/high-blood-pressure.aspx">https://www.bhf.org.uk/heart-health/conditions/high-blood-pressure.aspx</a></p>'),
	(2, 'en', 'Mood', 'images/libra/mood_amber.png', '<h1>Mood</h1>\r\n\r\n<h2 class="h-color">Keep this up!</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Your profile tells us that your general mood is good. Keep this up!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Feeling low can have an impact on our brain health.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Below you will find information to help you maintain you current overall mood level.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="" src="images/riskfactors/mood/img1.png" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>People with low mood often have more trouble concentrating and performing normal mental activities.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Low or depressed mood can be treated by eating a healthy diet, taking exercise, being more social and talking to a therapist. All these things will help improve your cognitive activity and in turn your cognitive function.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>People who feel depressed or anxious often have trouble sleeping. Poor sleep is known to reduce our cognitive function.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Cognitive function refers to memory, the ability to learn new information, process thoughts, speech and reading comprehension.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>Know your mood</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>People who are depressed may:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>feel sad or hopeless</li>\r\n	<li>lose interest or pleasure in life</li>\r\n	<li>feel guilty or have low self-worth</li>\r\n	<li>find their sleep pattern or appetite is disturbed</li>\r\n	<li>feel tired</li>\r\n	<li>have trouble concentrating</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Speak to your GP/health professional</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Contact support services</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Exercise and get outdoors. Visit our Physical Activity page <a href="infos-riskfactor.html?riskfactor=4">here</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="" src="images/riskfactors/mood/img2.png" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Eat a balanced diet. Visit our Diet page <a href="infos-riskfactor.html?riskfactor=9">here</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Avoid alcohol</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Get enough rest and sleep</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Talk to family and friends</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Socialise more. See information <a href="infos-riskfactor.html?riskfactor=8">here</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Getting enough quality sleep is good for your mood.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Here are some tips to help you get a good night&rsquo;s sleep:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Try to go to bed at the same time every night and get up at the same time every morning, even at the weekends!</li>\r\n	<li>Avoid watching TV or using a laptop, tablet or mobile phone in bed.</li>\r\n	<li>Don&rsquo;t go to bed hungry or on a full stomach.</li>\r\n	<li>Make sure your bedroom is cool, dark and quiet.</li>\r\n	<li>Limit daytime naps.</li>\r\n	<li>Be physically active each day.</li>\r\n	<li>Get help managing your stress.</li>\r\n	<li>Don&rsquo;t lie awake worrying about not sleeping. Get up, go to another room and read or watch something boring on the TV. When you start to feel tired, return to bed</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '<h1>Mood</h1>\r\n\r\n<h2 class="h-color">Room for improvement</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Your profile tells us that your general mood could be improved.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Feeling low can have an impact on our brain health.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Below you will find information to help you improve your overall mood.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You will also find your personalised plan.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="" src="images/riskfactors/mood/img1.png" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>People with low mood often have more trouble concentrating and performing normal mental activities.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Low or depressed mood can be treated by eating a healthy diet, taking exercise, being more social and talking to a therapist. All these things will help improve your cognitive activity and in turn your cognitive function.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>People who feel depressed or anxious often have trouble sleeping. Poor sleep is known to reduce our cognitive function.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Cognitive function refers to memory, the ability to learn new information, process thoughts, speech and reading comprehension.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>Know your mood</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>People who are depressed may:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>feel sad or hopeless</li>\r\n	<li>lose interest or pleasure in life</li>\r\n	<li>feel guilty or have low self-worth</li>\r\n	<li>find their sleep pattern or appetite is disturbed</li>\r\n	<li>feel tired</li>\r\n	<li>have trouble concentrating</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Speak to your GP/health professional</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Contact support services</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Exercise and get outdoors. Visit our Physical Activity page <a href="infos-riskfactor.html?riskfactor=4">here</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="" src="images/riskfactors/mood/img2.png" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Eat a balanced diet. Visit our Diet page <a href="infos-riskfactor.html?riskfactor=9">here</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Avoid alcohol</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Get enough rest and sleep</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Talk to family and friends</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Socialise more. See information <a href="infos-riskfactor.html?riskfactor=8">here</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Getting enough quality sleep is good for your mood.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Here are some tips to help you get a good night&rsquo;s sleep:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Try to go to bed at the same time every night and get up at the same time every morning, even at the weekends!</li>\r\n	<li>Avoid watching TV or using a laptop, tablet or mobile phone in bed.</li>\r\n	<li>Don&rsquo;t go to bed hungry or on a full stomach.</li>\r\n	<li>Make sure your bedroom is cool, dark and quiet.</li>\r\n	<li>Limit daytime naps.</li>\r\n	<li>Be physically active each day.</li>\r\n	<li>Get help managing your stress.</li>\r\n	<li>Don&rsquo;t lie awake worrying about not sleeping. Get up, go to another room and read or watch something boring on the TV. When you start to feel tired, return to bed</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '<h3>Further Supports:</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The following organisations provide information and support to people with mental health difficulties, their families and carers while promoting positive mental health in families, communities and the workplace.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a href="http://www.aware.ie">www.aware.ie</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href="http://www.mentalhealthireland.ie">www.mentalhealthireland.ie</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href="http://www.grow.ie">www.grow.ie</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href="http://www.mymind.org">www.mymind.org</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>A list of accredited counsellers in your local area:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a href="http://www.counsellingdirectory.ie">www.counsellingdirectory.ie</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Interactive web program designed to prevent/improve depression</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a href="http://www.moodgym.an.edu.au">www.moodgym.an.edu.au</a></li>\r\n</ul>'),
	(2, 'fr', 'Humeur', 'images/libra/mood_amber.png', '<h1>Humeur</h1>\r\n\r\n<h2 class="h-color">Continuez comme &ccedil;a !</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Votre profil nous informe que vous &ecirc;tes globalement de bonne humeur. Continuez comme &ccedil;a&nbsp;!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&Ecirc;tre d&eacute;prim&eacute; peut avoir des cons&eacute;quences sur la sant&eacute; de votre cerveau.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Vous trouverez ci-dessous des informations qui vous permettront d&rsquo;am&eacute;liorer votre humeur g&eacute;n&eacute;rale.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Vous y trouverez &eacute;galement votre programme personnalis&eacute;.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="" src="images/riskfactors/mood/img1.png" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Les personnes d&eacute;prim&eacute;es &eacute;prouvent bien souvent des difficult&eacute;s &agrave; se concentrer ainsi qu&rsquo;&agrave; effectuer des activit&eacute;s mentales simples.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>La tendance &agrave; la mauvaise humeur peut &ecirc;tre soign&eacute;e en adoptant une alimentation saine, en faisant de l&rsquo;exercice, en &eacute;tant plus sociable et en parlant &agrave; un th&eacute;rapeute.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Lorsqu&rsquo;on se sent d&eacute;prim&eacute; ou angoiss&eacute;, on a plus de mal &agrave; dormir. Un sommeil difficile est bien souvent &agrave; l&rsquo;origine de fonctions cognitives r&eacute;duites.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Le terme de fonctions cognitives renvoie &agrave; la m&eacute;moire, la capacit&eacute; d&rsquo;apprendre de nouvelles informations, de traiter les pens&eacute;es, ainsi que la compr&eacute;hension orale et &eacute;crite.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>&nbsp;</h3>\r\n\r\n<h3>Apprenez &agrave; conna&icirc;tre votre humeur</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Les personnes d&eacute;prim&eacute;es sont susceptibles de&nbsp;:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>ressentir de la tristesse ou du d&eacute;sespoir</li>\r\n	<li>se d&eacute;sint&eacute;resser de la vie et de n&rsquo;y prendre aucun plaisir</li>\r\n	<li>se sentir coupables ou perdre confiance en elles</li>\r\n	<li>voir leurs cycles de sommeil ou leur app&eacute;tit perturb&eacute;s</li>\r\n	<li>se sentir fatigu&eacute;es, ou</li>\r\n	<li>d&rsquo;&eacute;prouver des difficult&eacute;s &agrave; se concentrer.&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Parlez-en &agrave; votre m&eacute;decin ou &agrave; un professionnel de la sant&eacute;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Contactez des services de soutien</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Faites du sport, sortez. Pour visiter notre page d&eacute;di&eacute;e &agrave; l&rsquo;activit&eacute; physique, cliquez <a href="infos-riskfactor.html?riskfactor=4">ici</a>.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="" src="images/riskfactors/mood/img2.png" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Adoptez une alimentation &eacute;quilibr&eacute;e. Pour visiter notre page d&eacute;di&eacute;e &agrave; l&rsquo;alimentation, cliquez <a href="infos-riskfactor.html?riskfactor=9">ici</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Evitez de boire de l&rsquo;alcool.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Reposez-vous, dormez suffisamment.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Parlez &agrave; vos proches, votre famille, vos amis.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Sortez, voyez davantage de personnes. Pour plus d&rsquo;informations,<a href="infos-riskfactor.html?riskfactor=8"> cliquez ici</a>.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Le sommeil r&eacute;parateur est b&eacute;n&eacute;fique pour votre sant&eacute;.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Voici quelques astuces qui vous aideront &agrave; bien dormir la nuit&nbsp;:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Essayez de vous lever et d&rsquo;aller vous coucher &agrave; heure fixe, m&ecirc;me le weekend&nbsp;!</li>\r\n	<li>Evitez de regarder la t&eacute;l&eacute;vision ou de rester sur votre portable, votre tablette ou votre mobile lorsque vous &ecirc;tes couch&eacute;.</li>\r\n	<li>N&rsquo;allez pas vous coucher alors que vous avez faim ou trop mang&eacute;.</li>\r\n	<li>Assurez-vous que votre chambre est fra&icirc;che, calme et qu&rsquo;il n&rsquo;y a pas trop de lumi&egrave;re.</li>\r\n	<li>Essayez de limiter les siestes en journ&eacute;e.</li>\r\n	<li>Soyez tonique et maintenez votre corps actif au quotidien.</li>\r\n	<li>Faites-vous aider pour g&eacute;rer votre stress.</li>\r\n	<li>Ne restez pas allong&eacute; &agrave; vous ronger les sangs lorsque vous ne dormez pas&nbsp;; levez-vous, changez de pi&egrave;ce et lisez ou regardez un programme ennuyeux &agrave; la t&eacute;l&eacute;vision. Lorsque vous commencez &agrave; vous sentir fatigu&eacute;, retournez vous coucher.</li>\r\n</ul>', '<h1>Humeur&nbsp;</h1>\r\n\r\n<h2>Une am&eacute;lioration est possible</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Votre profil nous informe que votre humeur g&eacute;n&eacute;rale pourrait b&eacute;n&eacute;ficier de certaines am&eacute;liorations.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Etre d&eacute;prim&eacute; peut avoir des cons&eacute;quences sur la sant&eacute; de votre cerveau.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Vous trouverez ci-dessous des informations qui vous permettront d&rsquo;am&eacute;liorer votre humeur g&eacute;n&eacute;rale.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Vous y trouverez &eacute;galement votre programme personnalis&eacute;.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="" src="images/riskfactors/mood/img1.png" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Les personnes d&eacute;prim&eacute;es &eacute;prouvent bien souvent des difficult&eacute;s &agrave; se concentrer ainsi qu&rsquo;&agrave; effectuer des activit&eacute;s mentales simples.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>La tendance &agrave; la mauvaise humeur peut &ecirc;tre soign&eacute;e en adoptant une alimentation saine, en faisant de l&rsquo;exercice, en &eacute;tant plus sociable et en parlant &agrave; un th&eacute;rapeute.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Lorsqu&rsquo;on se sent d&eacute;prim&eacute; ou angoiss&eacute;, on a plus de mal &agrave; dormir. Un sommeil difficile est bien souvent &agrave; l&rsquo;origine de fonctions cognitives r&eacute;duites.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Le terme de fonctions cognitives renvoie &agrave; la m&eacute;moire, la capacit&eacute; d&rsquo;apprendre de nouvelles informations, de traiter les pens&eacute;es, ainsi que la compr&eacute;hension orale et &eacute;crite.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>&nbsp;</h3>\r\n\r\n<h3>Apprenez &agrave; conna&icirc;tre votre humeur</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Les personnes d&eacute;prim&eacute;es sont susceptibles de&nbsp;:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>ressentir de la tristesse ou du d&eacute;sespoir</li>\r\n	<li>se d&eacute;sint&eacute;resser de la vie et de n&rsquo;y prendre aucun plaisir</li>\r\n	<li>se sentir coupables ou perdre confiance en elles</li>\r\n	<li>voir leurs cycles de sommeil ou leur app&eacute;tit perturb&eacute;s</li>\r\n	<li>se sentir fatigu&eacute;es, ou</li>\r\n	<li>d&rsquo;&eacute;prouver des difficult&eacute;s &agrave; se concentrer.&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Parlez-en &agrave; votre m&eacute;decin ou &agrave; un professionnel de la sant&eacute;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Contactez des services de soutien</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Faites du sport, sortez. Pour visiter notre page d&eacute;di&eacute;e &agrave; l&rsquo;activit&eacute; physique, cliquez <a href="infos-riskfactor.html?riskfactor=4">ici</a>.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="" src="images/riskfactors/mood/img2.png" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Adoptez une alimentation &eacute;quilibr&eacute;e. Pour visiter notre page d&eacute;di&eacute;e &agrave; l&rsquo;alimentation, cliquez <a href="infos-riskfactor.html?riskfactor=9">ici</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Evitez de boire de l&rsquo;alcool.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Reposez-vous, dormez suffisamment.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Parlez &agrave; vos proches, votre famille, vos amis.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Sortez, voyez davantage de personnes. Pour plus d&rsquo;informations,<a href="infos-riskfactor.html?riskfactor=8"> cliquez ici</a>.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Le sommeil r&eacute;parateur est b&eacute;n&eacute;fique pour votre sant&eacute;.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Voici quelques astuces qui vous aideront &agrave; bien dormir la nuit&nbsp;:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Essayez de vous lever et d&rsquo;aller vous coucher &agrave; heure fixe, m&ecirc;me le weekend&nbsp;!</li>\r\n	<li>Evitez de regarder la t&eacute;l&eacute;vision ou de rester sur votre portable, votre tablette ou votre mobile lorsque vous &ecirc;tes couch&eacute;.</li>\r\n	<li>N&rsquo;allez pas vous coucher alors que vous avez faim ou trop mang&eacute;.</li>\r\n	<li>Assurez-vous que votre chambre est fra&icirc;che, calme et qu&rsquo;il n&rsquo;y a pas trop de lumi&egrave;re.</li>\r\n	<li>Essayez de limiter les siestes en journ&eacute;e.</li>\r\n	<li>Soyez tonique et maintenez votre corps actif au quotidien.</li>\r\n	<li>Faites-vous aider pour g&eacute;rer votre stress.</li>\r\n	<li>Ne restez pas allong&eacute; &agrave; vous ronger les sangs lorsque vous ne dormez pas&nbsp;; levez-vous, changez de pi&egrave;ce et lisez ou regardez un programme ennuyeux &agrave; la t&eacute;l&eacute;vision. Lorsque vous commencez &agrave; vous sentir fatigu&eacute;, retournez vous coucher.</li>\r\n</ul>', ' '),
	(2, 'sc', 'Mood', 'images/libra/mood_amber.png', '<h1>Mood</h1>\r\n\r\n<h2 class="h-color">Keep this up!</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Your profile tells us that your general mood is good. Keep this up!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Feeling low can have an impact on our brain health.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Below you will find information to help you maintain you current overall mood level.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="" src="images/riskfactors/mood/img1.png" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>People with low mood often have more trouble concentrating and performing normal mental activities.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Low or depressed mood can be treated by eating a healthy diet, taking exercise, being more social and talking to a therapist. All these things will help improve your cognitive activity and in turn your cognitive function.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>People who feel depressed or anxious often have trouble sleeping. Poor sleep is known to reduce our cognitive function.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Cognitive function refers to memory, the ability to learn new information, process thoughts, speech and reading comprehension.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>Know your mood</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>People who are depressed may:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>feel sad or hopeless</li>\r\n	<li>lose interest or pleasure in life</li>\r\n	<li>feel guilty or have low self-worth</li>\r\n	<li>find their sleep pattern or appetite is disturbed</li>\r\n	<li>feel tired</li>\r\n	<li>have trouble concentrating</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Speak to your GP/health professional</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Contact support services</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Exercise and get outdoors. Visit our Physical Activity page <a href="infos-riskfactor.html?riskfactor=4">here</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="" src="images/riskfactors/mood/img2.png" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Eat a balanced diet. Visit our Diet page <a href="infos-riskfactor.html?riskfactor=9">here</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Avoid alcohol</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Get enough rest and sleep</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Talk to family and friends</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Socialise more. See information <a href="infos-riskfactor.html?riskfactor=8">here</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Getting enough quality sleep is good for your mood.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Here are some tips to help you get a good night&rsquo;s sleep:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Try to go to bed at the same time every night and get up at the same time every morning, even at the weekends!</li>\r\n	<li>Avoid watching TV or using a laptop, tablet or mobile phone in bed.</li>\r\n	<li>Don&rsquo;t go to bed hungry or on a full stomach.</li>\r\n	<li>Make sure your bedroom is cool, dark and quiet.</li>\r\n	<li>Limit daytime naps.</li>\r\n	<li>Be physically active each day.</li>\r\n	<li>Get help managing your stress.</li>\r\n	<li>Don&rsquo;t lie awake worrying about not sleeping. Get up, go to another room and read or watch something boring on the TV. When you start to feel tired, return to bed</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '<h1>Mood</h1>\r\n\r\n<h2 class="h-color">Room for improvement</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Your profile tells us that your general mood could be improved.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Feeling low can have an impact on our brain health.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Below you will find information to help you improve your overall mood.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You will also find your personalised plan.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="" src="images/riskfactors/mood/img1.png" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>People with low mood often have more trouble concentrating and performing normal mental activities.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Low or depressed mood can be treated by eating a healthy diet, taking exercise, being more social and talking to a therapist. All these things will help improve your cognitive activity and in turn your cognitive function.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>People who feel depressed or anxious often have trouble sleeping. Poor sleep is known to reduce our cognitive function.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Cognitive function refers to memory, the ability to learn new information, process thoughts, speech and reading comprehension.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>Know your mood</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>People who are depressed may:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>feel sad or hopeless</li>\r\n	<li>lose interest or pleasure in life</li>\r\n	<li>feel guilty or have low self-worth</li>\r\n	<li>find their sleep pattern or appetite is disturbed</li>\r\n	<li>feel tired</li>\r\n	<li>have trouble concentrating</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Speak to your GP/health professional</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Contact support services</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Exercise and get outdoors. Visit our Physical Activity page <a href="infos-riskfactor.html?riskfactor=4">here</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="" src="images/riskfactors/mood/img2.png" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Eat a balanced diet. Visit our Diet page <a href="infos-riskfactor.html?riskfactor=9">here</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Avoid alcohol</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Get enough rest and sleep</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Talk to family and friends</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Socialise more. See information <a href="infos-riskfactor.html?riskfactor=8">here</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Getting enough quality sleep is good for your mood.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Here are some tips to help you get a good night&rsquo;s sleep:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Try to go to bed at the same time every night and get up at the same time every morning, even at the weekends!</li>\r\n	<li>Avoid watching TV or using a laptop, tablet or mobile phone in bed.</li>\r\n	<li>Don&rsquo;t go to bed hungry or on a full stomach.</li>\r\n	<li>Make sure your bedroom is cool, dark and quiet.</li>\r\n	<li>Limit daytime naps.</li>\r\n	<li>Be physically active each day.</li>\r\n	<li>Get help managing your stress.</li>\r\n	<li>Don&rsquo;t lie awake worrying about not sleeping. Get up, go to another room and read or watch something boring on the TV. When you start to feel tired, return to bed</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '<h3>Further Supports:</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Living Life is a free telephone service available to anyone over the age of 16 who is suffering from low mood, mild to moderate depression and/or anxiety:</p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href="http://www.nhs24.com/usefulresources/livinglife">http://www.nhs24.com/usefulresources/livinglife</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Living Life to the Full is an interactive online package based on cognitive behaviour therapy:</p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href="http://www.llttf.com/">http://www.llttf.com/</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>NHS information on depression:</p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href="http://www.nhs.uk/conditions/depression/Pages/Introduction.aspx">http://www.nhs.uk/conditions/depression/Pages/Introduction.aspx</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Mood gym. A free self-help program to teach cognitive behaviour therapy skills to people vulnerable to depression and anxiety:</p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href="https://moodgym.anu.edu.au/welcome">https://moodgym.anu.edu.au/welcome</a></p>'),
	(3, 'en', 'Diabetes', 'images/libra/diabetes-amber.png', '<h1>Diabetes</h1>\r\n\r\n<h2 class="h-color">Keep this up!</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Your profile tells us that you do not have diabetes. This is good news for your long term brain health!&nbsp; Below you will find information on lifestyle choices that can help prevent diabetes in the future.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Who is at risk?</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>You are more at risk of getting Type 2 diabetes if you are:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Over 40 years of age</li>\r\n	<li>Have a parent or brother/sister with diabetes</li>\r\n	<li>Had&nbsp;diabetes during a pregnancy</li>\r\n	<li>Are overweight</li>\r\n	<li>Do not take 30 minutes of exercise daily</li>\r\n	<li>Have high blood pressure</li>\r\n	<li>Have high cholesterol levels</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>What can I do?</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Eat regularly</li>\r\n	<li>Watch your serving size</li>\r\n	<li>Follow a healthy eating plan. One good plan is the Mediterranean Diet, which is low in refined sugars and fat. For more information, visit our Diet page <a href="infos-riskfactor.html?riskfactor=9">here</a><br />\r\n	<img alt="" src="images/riskfactors/diabetes/img2.png" /></li>\r\n	<li>Choose low-fat options when eating meat, poultry, dairy products and spread</li>\r\n	<li>Eat a wide variety of fresh fruit and vegetables</li>\r\n	<li>Choose wholegrain bread, pasta and cereals</li>\r\n	<li>Keep foods high in fat and sugar to a minimum</li>\r\n	<li>Get active by taking 30 minutes of physical exercise a day. For more information, visit our Physical Activity page <a href="infos-riskfactor.html?riskfactor=4">here</a><br />\r\n	<img alt="" src="images/riskfactors/diabetes/img3.png" /></li>\r\n</ul>', '<h1>Diabetes</h1>\r\n\r\n<h2 class="h-color">Remember to manage well</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Your profile tells us that you have diabetes.Besides taking medication, you can manage diabetes through diet and exercise. Below you will find information to help you.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you manage your diabetes well, you can protect your brain health and your overall health.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>You are more at risk of getting Type 2 diabetes if you are:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Over 40 years of age</li>\r\n	<li>Have a parent or brother/sister with diabetes</li>\r\n	<li>Had&nbsp;diabetes during a pregnancy</li>\r\n	<li>Are overweight</li>\r\n	<li>Do not take 30 minutes of exercise daily</li>\r\n	<li>Have high blood pressure</li>\r\n	<li>Have high cholesterol levels</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>What can I do?</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Eat regularly</li>\r\n	<li>Watch your serving size</li>\r\n	<li>Follow a healthy eating plan. One good plan is the Mediterranean Diet, which is low in refined sugars and fat. For more information, visit our Diet page <a href="infos-riskfactor.html?riskfactor=9">here</a><br />\r\n	<img alt="" src="images/riskfactors/diabetes/img2.png" /></li>\r\n	<li>Choose low-fat options when eating meat, poultry, dairy products and spread</li>\r\n	<li>Eat a wide variety of fresh fruit and vegetables</li>\r\n	<li>Choose wholegrain bread, pasta and cereals</li>\r\n	<li>Keep foods high in fat and sugar to a minimum</li>\r\n	<li>Get active by taking 30 minutes of physical exercise a day. For more information, visit our Physical Activity page <a href="infos-riskfactor.html?riskfactor=4">here</a><br />\r\n	<img alt="" src="images/riskfactors/diabetes/img3.png" /></li>\r\n</ul>', '<h3>Other Supports</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a href="http://www.diabetes.ie/">www.diabetes.ie</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Site provides information on attending a diabetic clinic, self-management, diet and exercise advice</p>'),
	(3, 'fr', 'Diabetes', 'images/libra/diabetes-amber.png', '<h1>Diabetes</h1>\r\n\r\n<h2 class="h-color">Continuez comme &ccedil;a&nbsp;! &nbsp;&nbsp;</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Votre profil nous annonce que vous n&rsquo;&ecirc;tes pas diab&eacute;tique. C&rsquo;est une bonne nouvelle pour la sant&eacute; &agrave; long terme de votre cerveau&nbsp;!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Ci-dessous, vous trouverez des informations sur les choix de vie qui permettent de pr&eacute;venir un diab&egrave;te dans le futur.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Vous avez plus de risques d&#39;&ecirc;tre atteint d&#39;un diab&egrave;te de type 2 si vous:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>avez plus de 40 ans</li>\r\n	<li>avez un parent diab&eacute;tique</li>\r\n	<li>avez eu du diab&egrave;te lors d&#39;une grossesse</li>\r\n	<li>&ecirc;tes en surpoids</li>\r\n	<li>ne faites pas 30 minutes de sport quotidien</li>\r\n	<li>avez de l&#39;hypertension</li>\r\n	<li>avez un taux de cholest&eacute;rol &eacute;lev&eacute;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>Que dois-je faire?</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Manger &agrave; heures r&eacute;guli&egrave;res</li>\r\n	<li>Surveiller la quantit&eacute; de ce que vous mangez</li>\r\n	<li>Suivre un r&eacute;gime alimentaire &eacute;quilibr&eacute;. Le r&eacute;gime alimentaire m&eacute;diterran&eacute;en, pauvre en sucre raffin&eacute; et en graisse, est un bon r&eacute;gime alimentaire. Pour plus d&#39;informations, consultez notre page sur le r&eacute;gime alimentaire ici.<br />\r\n	<img alt="" src="images/riskfactors/diabetes/img2.png" /></li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Choisir le moins gras quand vous mangez de la viande, de la volaille, des produits laitiers et des confitures/garnitures&nbsp;?</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Manger une grande vari&eacute;t&eacute; de l&eacute;gumes et de fruits frais.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Choisir du pain complet, des p&acirc;tes et des c&eacute;r&eacute;ales compl&egrave;tes.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Manger le moins possible d&rsquo;aliments gras et sucr&eacute;s</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Faire du sport 30 minutes par jour au moins. Pour plus d&rsquo;information, r&eacute;f&eacute;rez-vous &agrave; notre page sur l&rsquo;activit&eacute; physique <a href="infos-riskfactor.html?riskfactor=4">ici</a>.</p>\r\n	<img alt="" src="images/riskfactors/diabetes/img3.png" /></li>\r\n</ul>', '<h1>Diab&egrave;te</h1>\r\n\r\n<h2 class="h-color">Pensez &agrave; le surveiller&nbsp;</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Votre profil nous annonce que vous &ecirc;tes diab&eacute;tique. Outre la prise d&#39;un traitement, vous pouvez &eacute;quilibrer votre diab&egrave;te gr&acirc;ce &agrave; votre alimentation et votre pratique physique. Ci-dessous, vous trouverez des informations pour vous aider.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Si vous &eacute;quilibrez bien votre diab&egrave;te, vous pouvez pr&eacute;server la sant&eacute; de votre cerveau et votre sant&eacute; globale.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Vous avez plus de risques d&#39;&ecirc;tre atteint d&#39;un diab&egrave;te de type 2 si vous:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>avez plus de 40 ans</li>\r\n	<li>avez un parent diab&eacute;tique</li>\r\n	<li>avez eu du diab&egrave;te lors d&#39;une grossesse</li>\r\n	<li>&ecirc;tes en surpoids</li>\r\n	<li>ne faites pas 30 minutes de sport quotidien</li>\r\n	<li>avez de l&#39;hypertension</li>\r\n	<li>avez un taux de cholest&eacute;rol &eacute;lev&eacute;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>Que dois-je faire?</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Manger &agrave; heures r&eacute;guli&egrave;res</li>\r\n	<li>Surveiller la quantit&eacute; de ce que vous mangez</li>\r\n	<li>Suivre un r&eacute;gime alimentaire &eacute;quilibr&eacute;. Le r&eacute;gime alimentaire m&eacute;diterran&eacute;en, pauvre en sucre raffin&eacute; et en graisse, est un bon r&eacute;gime alimentaire. Pour plus d&#39;informations, consultez notre page sur le r&eacute;gime alimentaire ici.<br />\r\n	<img alt="" src="images/riskfactors/diabetes/img2.png" /></li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Choisir le moins gras quand vous mangez de la viande, de la volaille, des produits laitiers et des confitures/garnitures&nbsp;?</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Manger une grande vari&eacute;t&eacute; de l&eacute;gumes et de fruits frais.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Choisir du pain complet, des p&acirc;tes et des c&eacute;r&eacute;ales compl&egrave;tes.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Manger le moins possible d&rsquo;aliments gras et sucr&eacute;s</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Faire du sport 30 minutes par jour au moins. Pour plus d&rsquo;information, r&eacute;f&eacute;rez-vous &agrave; notre page sur l&rsquo;activit&eacute; physique <a href="infos-riskfactor.html?riskfactor=4">ici</a>.</p>\r\n	<img alt="" src="images/riskfactors/diabetes/img3.png" /></li>\r\n</ul>', ' '),
	(3, 'sc', 'Diabetes', 'images/libra/diabetes-amber.png', '<h1>Diabetes</h1>\r\n\r\n<h2 class="h-color">Keep this up!</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Your profile tells us that you do not have diabetes. This is good news for your long term brain health!&nbsp; Below you will find information on lifestyle choices that can help prevent diabetes in the future.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Who is at risk?</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>You are more at risk of getting Type 2 diabetes if you are:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Over 40 years of age</li>\r\n	<li>Have a parent or brother/sister with diabetes</li>\r\n	<li>Had&nbsp;diabetes during a pregnancy</li>\r\n	<li>Are overweight</li>\r\n	<li>Do not take 30 minutes of exercise daily</li>\r\n	<li>Have high blood pressure</li>\r\n	<li>Have high cholesterol levels</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>What can I do?</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Eat regularly</li>\r\n	<li>Watch your serving size</li>\r\n	<li>Follow a healthy eating plan. One good plan is the Mediterranean Diet, which is low in refined sugars and fat. For more information, visit our Diet page <a href="infos-riskfactor.html?riskfactor=9">here</a><br />\r\n	<img alt="" src="images/riskfactors/diabetes/img2.png" /></li>\r\n	<li>Choose low-fat options when eating meat, poultry, dairy products and spread</li>\r\n	<li>Eat a wide variety of fresh fruit and vegetables</li>\r\n	<li>Choose wholegrain bread, pasta and cereals</li>\r\n	<li>Keep foods high in fat and sugar to a minimum</li>\r\n	<li>Get active by taking 30 minutes of physical exercise a day. For more information, visit our Physical Activity page <a href="infos-riskfactor.html?riskfactor=4">here</a><br />\r\n	<img alt="" src="images/riskfactors/diabetes/img3.png" /></li>\r\n</ul>', '<h1>Diabetes</h1>\r\n\r\n<h2 class="h-color">Remember to manage well</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Your profile tells us that you have diabetes.Besides taking medication, you can manage diabetes through diet and exercise. Below you will find information to help you.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you manage your diabetes well, you can protect your brain health and your overall health.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>You are more at risk of getting Type 2 diabetes if you are:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Over 40 years of age</li>\r\n	<li>Have a parent or brother/sister with diabetes</li>\r\n	<li>Had&nbsp;diabetes during a pregnancy</li>\r\n	<li>Are overweight</li>\r\n	<li>Do not take 30 minutes of exercise daily</li>\r\n	<li>Have high blood pressure</li>\r\n	<li>Have high cholesterol levels</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>What can I do?</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Eat regularly</li>\r\n	<li>Watch your serving size</li>\r\n	<li>Follow a healthy eating plan. One good plan is the Mediterranean Diet, which is low in refined sugars and fat. For more information, visit our Diet page <a href="infos-riskfactor.html?riskfactor=9">here</a><br />\r\n	<img alt="" src="images/riskfactors/diabetes/img2.png" /></li>\r\n	<li>Choose low-fat options when eating meat, poultry, dairy products and spread</li>\r\n	<li>Eat a wide variety of fresh fruit and vegetables</li>\r\n	<li>Choose wholegrain bread, pasta and cereals</li>\r\n	<li>Keep foods high in fat and sugar to a minimum</li>\r\n	<li>Get active by taking 30 minutes of physical exercise a day. For more information, visit our Physical Activity page <a href="infos-riskfactor.html?riskfactor=4">here</a><br />\r\n	<img alt="" src="images/riskfactors/diabetes/img3.png" /></li>\r\n</ul>', '<h3>Other Supports</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Diabetes UK. Self-help charity for&nbsp;<em>diabetics</em>, includes information and diet advice:</p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href="http://www.diabetes.org.uk/">http://www.diabetes.org.uk/</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>NHS information about diabetes:</p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href="http://www.nhs.uk/Conditions/Diabetes/Pages/Diabetes.aspx">http://www.nhs.uk/Conditions/Diabetes/Pages/Diabetes.aspx</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>patient.co.uk &ndash; diabetes information:</p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href="http://www.patient.co.uk/doctor/diabetes-mellitus">http://www.patient.co.uk/doctor/diabetes-mellitus</a></p>'),
	(4, 'en', 'Physical Exercise', 'images/libra/physical_exercise_amber.png', '<h1>Physical Activity</h1>\r\n\r\n<h2 class="h-color">Keep this up!</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Your profile tells us that you are doing enough physical activity to help protect your brain health. Well done, keep this up!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Below you will find information on the importance of being physically active. You will also find tips to help you maintain your current levels of activity, you may also find new ways to continue being physically active.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Did you know?</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Being physically active is good for your brain health!</strong><br />\r\nBeing physically active is one of the most important steps you can take to improve your overall health and wellbeing.<br />\r\nResearchers have found a link between physical activity and brain health. They believe that exercise may help us preserve cognitive function and activity and in turn protect us against dementia.<br />\r\nPeople who take regular exercise lower their risk of dementia by up to 30%.<br />\r\nRegular physical exercise helps the blood flow to the brain.<br />\r\nIt also helps lower the risk of stroke, heart attack and diabetes. These are all risk factors for dementia.<br />\r\nBeing physically active can have many different health benefits.<br />\r\nAs well as reducing our risk of dementia, it can improve our mood and our overall level of fitness. It can also keep our hearts healthy.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Being active can also:&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Lower your risk of heart disease&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>Maintain and/or improve your cholesterol level, your blood sugar levels, and your blood pressure.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>What should you aim for?</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Healthy adults aged 18&ndash;64 should spend at least 150 minutes a week doing some type of moderate physical activity.</li>\r\n	<li>Another option is to spend at least 75 minutes a week doing some type of vigorous activity or a third option would be a combination of moderate and vigorous activity.</li>\r\n	<li>One way to get your recommended 150 minutes a week is to do 30 minutes of physical exercise five days of the week.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Moderate physical activities take a little effort, but you should be able to talk while doing them.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>They include:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>walking fast&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>water aerobics</li>\r\n	<li>riding a bike on level ground or with a few hills</li>\r\n	<li>playing tennis for fun</li>\r\n	<li>pushing a lawn mower</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Vigorous physical activities require a little more effort and make you breathe harder and faster.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>They include:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>running&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;jogging</li>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;aerobics</li>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;fast cycling</li>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;any tasks that require carrying, lifting or digging</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Be physically active throughout the day!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Be active while travelling:</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Get off the bus a stop earlier.</li>\r\n	<li>Go for a walk at lunchtime.</li>\r\n	<li>Leave the car at home and walk to the shops.&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>Take the stairs rather than the lift.</li>\r\n	<li>If you sit at a desk for most of the day, make sure you take a break every 30 minutes and stretch your legs.</li>\r\n	<li>Remember, gardening, washing the windows and washing the car all count as physical activity.</li>\r\n	<li>Do tasks around the house that involve lifting, carrying or digging.</li>\r\n	<li>Walk the dog more often.</li>\r\n	<li>Push a pram while walking. If you know a new parent, offer to take the baby for a walk!</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="" src="images/riskfactors/physical/bike.jpg" /></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Have fun!</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>If running is not for you, you might like to try an aerobics class or some exercise classes. Another fun option is a dance class.</li>\r\n	<li>Taking up yoga is another way to improve your physical health. It also has many benefits for your mental health.</li>\r\n	<li>Remember, small changes to your daily routine can make a big difference.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="" src="images/riskfactors/physical/yoga.jpg" /></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Move around!</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Get active and sit less.</li>\r\n	<li>You can start by spending less time sitting at your computer or in front of the television.</li>\r\n	<li>Do 30 minutes of physical activity on five days of the week.</li>\r\n	<li>Go for a bicycle ride.</li>\r\n	<li>Invite friends to join you in a dance or exercise class.</li>\r\n	<li>Go for a quick jog or brisk walk for 15 minutes before breakfast every day.</li>\r\n	<li>Remember to choose something you enjoy. You&rsquo;ll be much more likely to keep it up then.</li>\r\n	<li>You could also check out local community noticeboards to see if there are any running groups in your area. Running groups have become quite common and offer beginners the chance to start at an easy pace and gradually increase. There are many fun 5k runs/walks around the country every weekend. Joining a running club is also a great way to meet new people.</li>\r\n</ul>', '<h1>Physical Activity</h1>\r\n\r\n<h2 class="h-color">Room for improvement</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Your profile tells us that you could take more exercise than you now do.<br />\r\nMaking small changes now could make a big difference to your brain health in later years.<br />\r\nBelow you will find information to get you started or to help you take more exercise than you now do.<br />\r\nClick on My Goals to see your personalised plan.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Did you know?</h3>\r\n\r\n	<strong>Being physically active is good for your brain health!</strong><br />\r\n	Being physically active is one of the most important steps you can take to improve your overall health and wellbeing.<br />\r\n	Researchers have found a link between physical activity and brain health. They believe that exercise may help us preserve cognitive function and activity and in turn protect us against dementia.<br />\r\n	People who take regular exercise lower their risk of dementia by up to 30%.<br />\r\n	Regular physical exercise helps the blood flow to the brain.<br />\r\n	It also helps lower the risk of stroke, heart attack and diabetes. These are all risk factors for dementia.<br />\r\n	Being physically active can have many different health benefits.<br />\r\n	As well as reducing our risk of dementia, it can improve our mood and our overall level of fitness. It can also keep our hearts healthy.&nbsp;<br />\r\n\r\n<p>Being active can also:&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Lower your risk of heart disease&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>Maintain and/or improve your cholesterol level, your blood sugar levels, and your blood pressure.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>What should you aim for?</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Healthy adults aged 18&ndash;64 should spend at least 150 minutes a week doing some type of moderate physical activity.</li>\r\n	<li>Another option is to spend at least 75 minutes a week doing some type of vigorous activity or a third option would be a combination of moderate and vigorous activity.</li>\r\n	<li>One way to get your recommended 150 minutes a week is to do 30 minutes of physical exercise five days of the week.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Moderate physical activities take a little effort, but you should be able to talk while doing them.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>They include:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>walking fast</li>\r\n	<li>water aerobics</li>\r\n	<li>riding a bike on level ground or with a few hills</li>\r\n	<li>playing tennis for fun</li>\r\n	<li>pushing a lawn mower</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Vigorous physical activities require a little more effort and make you breathe harder and faster.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>They include:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>running</li>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;jogging</li>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;aerobics</li>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;fast cycling</li>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;any tasks that require carrying, lifting or digging</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Be physically active throughout the day!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Be active while travelling:</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Get off the bus a stop earlier.</li>\r\n	<li>Go for a walk at lunchtime.</li>\r\n	<li>Leave the car at home and walk to the shops.&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>Take the stairs rather than the lift.</li>\r\n	<li>If you sit at a desk for most of the day, make sure you take a break every 30 minutes and stretch your legs.</li>\r\n	<li>Remember, gardening, washing the windows and washing the car all count as physical activity.</li>\r\n	<li>Do tasks around the house that involve lifting, carrying or digging.</li>\r\n	<li>Walk the dog more often.</li>\r\n	<li>Push a pram while walking. If you know a new parent, offer to take the baby for a walk!</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><img src="images/riskfactors/physical/bike.jpg" alt="" /></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Have fun!</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>If running is not for you, you might like to try an aerobics class or some exercise classes. Another fun option is a dance class.</li>\r\n	<li>Taking up yoga is another way to improve your physical health. It also has many benefits for your mental health.</li>\r\n	<li>Remember, small changes to your daily routine can make a big difference.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><img src="images/riskfactors/physical/yoga.jpg" alt="" /></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Move around!</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Get active and sit less.</li>\r\n	<li>You can start by spending less time sitting at your computer or in front of the television.</li>\r\n	<li>Do 30 minutes of physical activity on five days of the week.</li>\r\n	<li>Go for a bicycle ride.</li>\r\n	<li>Invite friends to join you in a dance or exercise class.</li>\r\n	<li>Go for a quick jog or brisk walk for 15 minutes before breakfast every day.</li>\r\n	<li>Remember to choose something you enjoy. You&rsquo;ll be much more likely to keep it up then.</li>\r\n	<li>You could also check out local community noticeboards to see if there are any running groups in your area. Running groups have become quite common and offer beginners the chance to start at an easy pace and gradually increase. There are many fun 5k runs/walks around the country every weekend. Joining a running club is also a great way to meet new people.</li>\r\n	<li>If you are not physically active now, you will benefit by starting. Even a small amount of exercise at first is better than doing nothing at all.</li>\r\n	<li>You can start slowly and increase the amount you do.</li>\r\n</ul>', '<h3>Further Supports</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><a href="http://www.getirelandactive.ie/">www.getirelandactive.ie</a></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>This site offers information and support on physical activity. It also provides information on local and national running/walking groups</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;<a href="http://www.getirelandwalking.ie/">www.getirelandwalking.ie</a></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Offers tips and advice on setting up walking groups and links to existing groups in your locality&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>'),
	(4, 'fr', 'Activit physique', 'images/libra/physical_exercise_amber.png', '<h1>Activit&eacute; physique</h1>\r\n\r\n<h2>Continuez comme &ccedil;a&nbsp;!</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Votre profil nous annonce que vous faites suffisamment d&rsquo;activit&eacute; physique pour vous aider &agrave; prot&eacute;ger votre sant&eacute; c&eacute;r&eacute;brale. Bravo, continuez comme &ccedil;a&nbsp;!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Vous trouverez ci-dessous des informations concernant l&rsquo;importance d&rsquo;&ecirc;tre actif physiquement. Vous trouverez &eacute;galement des conseils pour vous aider &agrave; maintenir votre niveau actuel d&rsquo;activit&eacute;, ainsi que de nouvelles fa&ccedil;ons de continuer &agrave; &ecirc;tre physiquement actif.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Le saviez-vous&nbsp;?</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Etre physiquement actif est bon pour votre sant&eacute; c&eacute;r&eacute;brale&nbsp;!</strong><br />\r\nEtre actif physiquement est l&rsquo;une des choses les plus importantes que vous pouvez faire pour am&eacute;liorer votre sant&eacute; g&eacute;n&eacute;rale et votre bien-&ecirc;tre.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Les chercheurs ont trouv&eacute; un lien entre l&rsquo;activit&eacute; physique et la sant&eacute; c&eacute;r&eacute;brale. Ils pensent que faire de l&rsquo;exercice peut nous aider &agrave; pr&eacute;server notre fonctionnement cognitif et notre activit&eacute; cognitive, et en retour nous prot&eacute;ger contre la d&eacute;mence.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Les personnes qui font r&eacute;guli&egrave;rement de l&rsquo;exercice diminuent jusqu&rsquo;&agrave; 30% leur risque de d&eacute;mence.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Un exercice physique r&eacute;gulier aide le sang &agrave; circuler jusqu&rsquo;au cerveau.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Il aide &eacute;galement &agrave; diminuer le risque d&rsquo;accident vasculaire, d&rsquo;infarctus ou de diab&egrave;te, qui sont tous des facteurs de risque de d&eacute;mence.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Etre actif physiquement peut avoir de nombreux b&eacute;n&eacute;fices diff&eacute;rents sur la sant&eacute;.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Cela peut r&eacute;duire notre risque de d&eacute;mence, aussi bien qu&rsquo;am&eacute;liorer notre humeur et notre forme physique. Cela peut &eacute;galement garder notre c&oelig;ur en bonne sant&eacute;.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Etre actif peut &eacute;galement&nbsp;:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Diminuer votre risque de maladie cardiaque</li>\r\n	<li>Maintenir et/ou am&eacute;liorer votre taux de cholest&eacute;rol, vos niveaux de glucose, et votre tension art&eacute;rielle</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>&nbsp;</h3>\r\n\r\n<h3>Quels objectifs devez-vous vous fixer&nbsp;?</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Des adultes de 18 &agrave; 64 ans en bonne sant&eacute; doivent passer au moins 2h30 par semaine&nbsp; &agrave; effectuer une activit&eacute; physique mod&eacute;r&eacute;e.</li>\r\n	<li>Une autre option est de passer au moins 1h15 par semaine &agrave; faire une activit&eacute; physique vigoureuse, ou une troisi&egrave;me option serait une combinaison d&rsquo;activit&eacute; mod&eacute;r&eacute;e et vigoureuse.</li>\r\n	<li>Une fa&ccedil;on d&rsquo;arriver aux 2h30 par semaine est de faire 30 minutes d&rsquo;exercice physique sur 5 jours de la semaine.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Les activit&eacute;s physiques mod&eacute;r&eacute;es demandent un peu d&rsquo;effort, mais vous devez &ecirc;tre capable de parler en m&ecirc;me temps que vous les effectuez.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Elles incluent&nbsp;:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>La marche rapide</li>\r\n	<li>La gymnastique aquatique</li>\r\n	<li>Le cyclisme sur terrain plat ou avec peu de pente</li>\r\n	<li>Le tennis par amusement</li>\r\n	<li>Pousser une tondeuse &agrave; gazon</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Les activit&eacute;s physiques vigoureuses requi&egrave;rent un peu plus d&rsquo;efforts, et vous font respirer plus difficilement et plus vite.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Elles incluent&nbsp;:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>La course rapide</li>\r\n	<li>Le jogging</li>\r\n	<li>La gymnastique</li>\r\n	<li>Le cyclisme rapide</li>\r\n	<li>Toute les activit&eacute;s qui n&eacute;cessitent de porter, soulever ou creuser</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Soyez actif tout au long de la journ&eacute;e&nbsp;!</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>&nbsp;</h3>\r\n\r\n<h3>Soyez actif lors de vos d&eacute;placements&nbsp;:</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Descendez du bus un arr&ecirc;t plus t&ocirc;t</li>\r\n	<li>Allez marcher lors de la pause-d&eacute;jeuner</li>\r\n	<li>Laissez votre voiture &agrave; la maison et aller faire les boutiques &agrave; pied</li>\r\n	<li>Prenez les escaliers plut&ocirc;t que l&rsquo;ascenseur</li>\r\n	<li>Si vous &ecirc;tes assis &agrave; un bureau la majeure partie de la journ&eacute;e, soyez s&ucirc;r de faire une pause toutes les 30 minutes et &eacute;tirez vos jambes.</li>\r\n	<li>Rappelez-vous que jardiner, laver les fen&ecirc;tre et laver la voiture compte pour les activit&eacute;s physiques</li>\r\n	<li>Faites les activit&eacute;s &agrave; la maison qui impliquent de porter ou de soulever des objets, ou de creuser</li>\r\n	<li>Promenez le chien plus souvent.</li>\r\n	<li>Poussez un landau lorsque vous marchez. Si vous connaissez un nouveau parent, proposez-lui de promener le b&eacute;b&eacute;&nbsp;!</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="" src="images/riskfactors/physical/bike.jpg" /></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Amusez-vous !</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Si courir n&rsquo;est pas pour vous, vous pourriez appr&eacute;cier de prendre des cours de gymnastique ou des cours d&rsquo;activit&eacute; physique. Une autre option amusante est de prendre des cours de danse.</li>\r\n	<li>Se mettre au yoga est une autre fa&ccedil;on d&rsquo;am&eacute;liorer votre sant&eacute; physique. Cela a &eacute;galement de nombreux b&eacute;n&eacute;fices pour votre sant&eacute; mentale.</li>\r\n	<li>Rappelez-vous, de petits changements &agrave; vos habitudes quotidiennes peuvent faire une grande diff&eacute;rence.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="" src="images/riskfactors/physical/yoga.jpg" /></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Bougez&nbsp;!</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Soyez actifs et moins assis.</li>\r\n	<li>Vous pouvez commencer en passant moins de temps assis devant votre ordinateur ou devant la t&eacute;l&eacute;vision.</li>\r\n	<li>Faites 30 minutes d&rsquo;activit&eacute; physique sur 5 jours de la semaine.</li>\r\n	<li>Promenez-vous en v&eacute;lo.</li>\r\n	<li>Invitez des amis &agrave; vous rejoindre pour des cours de danse ou d&rsquo;activit&eacute; physique.</li>\r\n	<li>Allez faire un jogging court ou une promenade &agrave; bon pas pendant 15 minutes avant de prendre le petit d&eacute;jeuner.</li>\r\n	<li>Rappelez-vous de choisir quelque chose que vous appr&eacute;ciez. Cela vous sera plus facile de continuer &agrave; le faire.</li>\r\n	<li>Vous pouvez &eacute;galement regarder les activit&eacute;s communautaires locales pour voir s&rsquo;il existe des clubs de course &agrave; pied dans votre secteur. Les clubs de course &agrave; pied sont devenus assez courants, et permettent aux d&eacute;butants de d&eacute;buter &agrave; un rythme facile qui augmentera progressivement. Rejoindre un club de course &agrave; pied est &eacute;galement une bonne fa&ccedil;on de rencontrer de nouvelles personnes.</li>\r\n</ul>', '<h1>Activit&eacute; physique</h1>\r\n\r\n<h2>Une am&eacute;lioration est possible</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Votre profil nous annonce que vous pourriez faire plus d&rsquo;exercice.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Mettre en place de petits changements d&egrave;s &agrave; pr&eacute;sent pourrait faire une grande diff&eacute;rence au niveau de votre sant&eacute; c&eacute;r&eacute;brale d&rsquo;ici quelques ann&eacute;es.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Vous trouverez ci-dessous des informations pour vous aider &agrave; commencer ou &agrave; faire plus d&rsquo;exercice physique.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Cliquez sur Mes Objectifs pour voir votre plan personnalis&eacute;.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Le saviez-vous&nbsp;?</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Etre physiquement actif est bon pour votre sant&eacute; c&eacute;r&eacute;brale&nbsp;!</strong><br />\r\nEtre actif physiquement est l&r