;butants de d&eacute;buter &agrave; un rythme facile qui augmentera progressivement. Rejoindre un club de course &agrave; pied est &eacute;galement une bonne fa&ccedil;on de rencontrer de nouvelles personnes.</li>\r\n	<li>Si vous n&rsquo;&ecirc;tes pas physiquement actif en ce moment, vous obtiendrez des b&eacute;n&eacute;fices en commen&ccedil;ant. M&ecirc;me une quantit&eacute; r&eacute;duite d&rsquo;exercice au d&eacute;but est meilleure que de ne rien faire du tout.</li>\r\n	<li>Vous pouvez commencer doucement, et augmenter progressivement votre quantit&eacute; d&rsquo;exercice.</li>\r\n</ul>', ' '),
	(4, 'sc', 'Physical Exercise', 'images/libra/physical_exercise_amber.png', '<h1>Physical Activity</h1>\r\n\r\n<h2 class="h-color">Keep this up!</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Your profile tells us that you are doing enough physical activity to help protect your brain health. Well done, keep this up!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Below you will find information on the importance of being physically active. You will also find tips to help you maintain your current levels of activity, you may also find new ways to continue being physically active.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Did you know?</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Being physically active is good for your brain health!</strong><br />\r\nBeing physically active is one of the most important steps you can take to improve your overall health and wellbeing.<br />\r\nResearchers have found a link between physical activity and brain health. They believe that exercise may help us preserve cognitive function and activity and in turn protect us against dementia.<br />\r\nPeople who take regular exercise lower their risk of dementia by up to 30%.<br />\r\nRegular physical exercise helps the blood flow to the brain.<br />\r\nIt also helps lower the risk of stroke, heart attack and diabetes. These are all risk factors for dementia.<br />\r\nBeing physically active can have many different health benefits.<br />\r\nAs well as reducing our risk of dementia, it can improve our mood and our overall level of fitness. It can also keep our hearts healthy.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Being active can also:&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Lower your risk of heart disease&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>Maintain and/or improve your cholesterol level, your blood sugar levels, and your blood pressure.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>What should you aim for?</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Healthy adults aged 18&ndash;64 should spend at least 150 minutes a week doing some type of moderate physical activity.</li>\r\n	<li>Another option is to spend at least 75 minutes a week doing some type of vigorous activity or a third option would be a combination of moderate and vigorous activity.</li>\r\n	<li>One way to get your recommended 150 minutes a week is to do 30 minutes of physical exercise five days of the week.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Moderate physical activities take a little effort, but you should be able to talk while doing them.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>They include:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>walking fast&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>water aerobics</li>\r\n	<li>riding a bike on level ground or with a few hills</li>\r\n	<li>playing tennis for fun</li>\r\n	<li>pushing a lawn mower</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Vigorous physical activities require a little more effort and make you breathe harder and faster.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>They include:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>running&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;jogging</li>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;aerobics</li>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;fast cycling</li>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;any tasks that require carrying, lifting or digging</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Be physically active throughout the day!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Be active while travelling:</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Get off the bus a stop earlier.</li>\r\n	<li>Go for a walk at lunchtime.</li>\r\n	<li>Leave the car at home and walk to the shops.&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>Take the stairs rather than the lift.</li>\r\n	<li>If you sit at a desk for most of the day, make sure you take a break every 30 minutes and stretch your legs.</li>\r\n	<li>Remember, gardening, washing the windows and washing the car all count as physical activity.</li>\r\n	<li>Do tasks around the house that involve lifting, carrying or digging.</li>\r\n	<li>Walk the dog more often.</li>\r\n	<li>Push a pram while walking. If you know a new parent, offer to take the baby for a walk!</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="" src="images/riskfactors/physical/bike.jpg" /></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Have fun!</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>If running is not for you, you might like to try an aerobics class or some exercise classes. Another fun option is a dance class.</li>\r\n	<li>Taking up yoga is another way to improve your physical health. It also has many benefits for your mental health.</li>\r\n	<li>Remember, small changes to your daily routine can make a big difference.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="" src="images/riskfactors/physical/yoga.jpg" /></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Move around!</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Get active and sit less.</li>\r\n	<li>You can start by spending less time sitting at your computer or in front of the television.</li>\r\n	<li>Do 30 minutes of physical activity on five days of the week.</li>\r\n	<li>Go for a bicycle ride.</li>\r\n	<li>Invite friends to join you in a dance or exercise class.</li>\r\n	<li>Go for a quick jog or brisk walk for 15 minutes before breakfast every day.</li>\r\n	<li>Remember to choose something you enjoy. You&rsquo;ll be much more likely to keep it up then.</li>\r\n	<li>You could also check out local community noticeboards to see if there are any running groups in your area. Running groups have become quite common and offer beginners the chance to start at an easy pace and gradually increase. There are many fun 5k runs/walks around the country every weekend. Joining a running club is also a great way to meet new people.</li>\r\n</ul>', '<h1>Physical Activity</h1>\r\n\r\n<h2 class="h-color">Room for improvement</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Your profile tells us that you could take more exercise than you now do.<br />\r\nMaking small changes now could make a big difference to your brain health in later years.<br />\r\nBelow you will find information to get you started or to help you take more exercise than you now do.<br />\r\nClick on My Goals to see your personalised plan.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Did you know?</h3>\r\n\r\n	<strong>Being physically active is good for your brain health!</strong><br />\r\n	Being physically active is one of the most important steps you can take to improve your overall health and wellbeing.<br />\r\n	Researchers have found a link between physical activity and brain health. They believe that exercise may help us preserve cognitive function and activity and in turn protect us against dementia.<br />\r\n	People who take regular exercise lower their risk of dementia by up to 30%.<br />\r\n	Regular physical exercise helps the blood flow to the brain.<br />\r\n	It also helps lower the risk of stroke, heart attack and diabetes. These are all risk factors for dementia.<br />\r\n	Being physically active can have many different health benefits.<br />\r\n	As well as reducing our risk of dementia, it can improve our mood and our overall level of fitness. It can also keep our hearts healthy.&nbsp;<br />\r\n\r\n<p>Being active can also:&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Lower your risk of heart disease&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>Maintain and/or improve your cholesterol level, your blood sugar levels, and your blood pressure.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>What should you aim for?</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Healthy adults aged 18&ndash;64 should spend at least 150 minutes a week doing some type of moderate physical activity.</li>\r\n	<li>Another option is to spend at least 75 minutes a week doing some type of vigorous activity or a third option would be a combination of moderate and vigorous activity.</li>\r\n	<li>One way to get your recommended 150 minutes a week is to do 30 minutes of physical exercise five days of the week.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Moderate physical activities take a little effort, but you should be able to talk while doing them.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>They include:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>walking fast</li>\r\n	<li>water aerobics</li>\r\n	<li>riding a bike on level ground or with a few hills</li>\r\n	<li>playing tennis for fun</li>\r\n	<li>pushing a lawn mower</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Vigorous physical activities require a little more effort and make you breathe harder and faster.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>They include:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>running</li>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;jogging</li>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;aerobics</li>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;fast cycling</li>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;any tasks that require carrying, lifting or digging</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Be physically active throughout the day!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Be active while travelling:</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Get off the bus a stop earlier.</li>\r\n	<li>Go for a walk at lunchtime.</li>\r\n	<li>Leave the car at home and walk to the shops.&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>Take the stairs rather than the lift.</li>\r\n	<li>If you sit at a desk for most of the day, make sure you take a break every 30 minutes and stretch your legs.</li>\r\n	<li>Remember, gardening, washing the windows and washing the car all count as physical activity.</li>\r\n	<li>Do tasks around the house that involve lifting, carrying or digging.</li>\r\n	<li>Walk the dog more often.</li>\r\n	<li>Push a pram while walking. If you know a new parent, offer to take the baby for a walk!</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><img src="images/riskfactors/physical/bike.jpg" alt="" /></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Have fun!</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>If running is not for you, you might like to try an aerobics class or some exercise classes. Another fun option is a dance class.</li>\r\n	<li>Taking up yoga is another way to improve your physical health. It also has many benefits for your mental health.</li>\r\n	<li>Remember, small changes to your daily routine can make a big difference.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><img src="images/riskfactors/physical/yoga.jpg" alt="" /></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Move around!</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Get active and sit less.</li>\r\n	<li>You can start by spending less time sitting at your computer or in front of the television.</li>\r\n	<li>Do 30 minutes of physical activity on five days of the week.</li>\r\n	<li>Go for a bicycle ride.</li>\r\n	<li>Invite friends to join you in a dance or exercise class.</li>\r\n	<li>Go for a quick jog or brisk walk for 15 minutes before breakfast every day.</li>\r\n	<li>Remember to choose something you enjoy. You&rsquo;ll be much more likely to keep it up then.</li>\r\n	<li>You could also check out local community noticeboards to see if there are any running groups in your area. Running groups have become quite common and offer beginners the chance to start at an easy pace and gradually increase. There are many fun 5k runs/walks around the country every weekend. Joining a running club is also a great way to meet new people.</li>\r\n	<li>If you are not physically active now, you will benefit by starting. Even a small amount of exercise at first is better than doing nothing at all.</li>\r\n	<li>You can start slowly and increase the amount you do.</li>\r\n</ul>', '<h3>Further Supports</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Active Scotland has been developed by NHS Scotland as a tool to support the physical activity workforce, primary care staff and allied health professionals working with patients to answer the question &quot;where do I go to be active?&quot;:</p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href="http://www.activescotland.org.uk/">http://www.activescotland.org.uk/</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Scottish Government&#39;s &quot;Take Life On Campaign&quot; suggests small, achievable lifestyle changes that can help you feel better and improve your health:</p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href="http://www.takelifeon.co.uk/">http://www.takelifeon.co.uk/</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>British Heart Foundation advice on physical activity:</p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href="http://www.bhf.org.uk/heart-health/prevention/staying-active.aspx">http://www.bhf.org.uk/heart-health/prevention/staying-active.aspx</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>NHS information on health and fitness:</p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href="http://www.nhs.uk/livewell/fitness/Pages/Fitnesshome.aspx">http://www.nhs.uk/livewell/fitness/Pages/Fitnesshome.aspx</a></p>'),
	(5, 'en', 'Smoking', 'images/libra/smoking_amber.png', '<h1>Smoking</h1>\r\n\r\n<h2 class="h-color">Keep this up!</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Your profile tells us that you do not smoke. Keep this up!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Smoking increases blood pressure and puts you at risk of heart disease. It can also affect your brain health. Evidence tells us that smoking in mid-life increases the risk of developing dementia in later years.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="" src="images/riskfactors/smoking/img.png" /></p>', '<h1>Smoking</h1>\r\n\r\n<h2 class="h-color">Room for improvement</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Your profile tells us you are a current smoker.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Smoking increases blood pressure and puts you at risk of heart disease. It can also affect your brain health. Evidence tells us that smoking in mid-life increases the risk of developing dementia in later years.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Making a change will improve your overall health and your brain health.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="" src="images/riskfactors/smoking/img.png" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>You may find it hard to quit smoking, but remember that many people have stopped with the right help</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>If you can&rsquo;t quit smoking altogether, then try cutting down. </strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Start by smoking one less cigarette a day. That is seven fewer cigarettes per week. The next week, cut two cigarettes per day.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Many people feel that smoking helps them cope with stress. </strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Look for other ways to manage stress. See our </strong><a href="infos-riskfactor.html?riskfactor=2"><strong>Mood</strong></a><strong><a href="infos-riskfactor.html?riskfactor=2"> page</a> for support and advice.</strong></p>', ''),
	(5, 'fr', 'Consommation de tabac', 'images/libra/smoking_amber.png', '<h1>Consommation de tabac</h1>\r\n\r\n<h2>Continuez comme &ccedil;a!</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Votre profil nous annonce que vous &ecirc;tes fumeur. Continuez comme &ccedil;a&nbsp;!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Fumer augmente la tension art&eacute;rielle et vous place dans une situation &agrave; risque de maladie cardiaque. Cela peut &eacute;galement affecter votre sant&eacute; c&eacute;r&eacute;brale. Les &eacute;tudes scientifiques nous fournissent la preuve que fumer &agrave; l&rsquo;&acirc;ge adulte augmente le risque de d&eacute;velopper une d&eacute;mence en vieillissant.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="" src="images/riskfactors/smoking/img.png" /></p>', '<h1>Consommation de tabac</h1>\r\n\r\n<h2>Une am&eacute;lioration est possible</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Votre profil nous annonce que vous &ecirc;tes fumeur.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Fumer augmente la tension art&eacute;rielle et vous place dans une situation &agrave; risque de maladie cardiaque. Cela peut &eacute;galement affecter votre sant&eacute; c&eacute;r&eacute;brale. Les &eacute;tudes scientifiques nous fournissent la preuve que fumer &agrave; l&rsquo;&acirc;ge adulte augmente le risque de d&eacute;velopper une d&eacute;mence en vieillissant</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Faire un changement am&eacute;liorera votre sant&eacute; g&eacute;n&eacute;rale et votre sant&eacute; c&eacute;r&eacute;brale.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="" src="images/riskfactors/smoking/img.png" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Vous pourriez trouver &ccedil;a difficile d&rsquo;arr&ecirc;ter de fumer, mais rappelez-vous que de nombreuses personnes ont arr&ecirc;t&eacute; gr&acirc;ce &agrave; une aide appropri&eacute;e.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Si vous n&rsquo;arrivez pas &agrave; arr&ecirc;ter de fumer compl&egrave;tement, alors essayer de ralentir.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Commencez par fumer une cigarette en moins par jour. Cela repr&eacute;sente 7 cigarettes en moins par semaine. La semaine suivante, enlevez 2 cigarettes par jour.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>De nombreuses personnes ont l&rsquo;impression que fumer les aide &agrave; g&eacute;rer leur stress.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Cherchez d&rsquo;autres fa&ccedil;ons de g&eacute;rer le stress. Regardez votre page <a href="http://">Humeur </a>pour de l&rsquo;aide et des conseils.</strong></p>', ' '),
	(5, 'sc', 'Smoking', 'images/libra/smoking_amber.png', '<h1>Smoking</h1>\r\n\r\n<h2 class="h-color">Keep this up!</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Your profile tells us that you do not smoke. Keep this up!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Smoking increases blood pressure and puts you at risk of heart disease. It can also affect your brain health. Evidence tells us that smoking in mid-life increases the risk of developing dementia in later years.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="" src="images/riskfactors/smoking/img.png" /></p>', '<h1>Smoking</h1>\r\n\r\n<h2 class="h-color">Room for improvement</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Your profile tells us you are a current smoker.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Smoking increases blood pressure and puts you at risk of heart disease. It can also affect your brain health. Evidence tells us that smoking in mid-life increases the risk of developing dementia in later years.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Making a change will improve your overall health and your brain health.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="" src="images/riskfactors/smoking/img.png" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>You may find it hard to quit smoking, but remember that many people have stopped with the right help</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>If you can&rsquo;t quit smoking altogether, then try cutting down. </strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Start by smoking one less cigarette a day. That is seven fewer cigarettes per week. The next week, cut two cigarettes per day.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Many people feel that smoking helps them cope with stress. </strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Look for other ways to manage stress. See our </strong><a href="infos-riskfactor.html?riskfactor=2"><strong>Mood</strong></a><strong><a href="infos-riskfactor.html?riskfactor=2"> page</a> for support and advice.</strong></p>', '<h3>Further Supports</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Smokeline is Scotland&#39;s national stop smoking helpline, open every day from 8am to 10pm:</p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href="http://www.canstopsmoking.com/">http://www.canstopsmoking.com/</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>NHS information on stopping smoking:</p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href="http://www.nhs.uk/Livewell/smoking/Pages/NHS-stop-smoking-adviser.aspx">http://www.nhs.uk/Livewell/smoking/Pages/NHS-stop-smoking-adviser.aspx</a></p>'),
	(6, 'en', 'Drinking', 'images/libra/drinking_amber.png', '<h1>Alcohol</h1>\r\n\r\n<h2 class="h-color">Keep this up!</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Your profile tells us that your alcohol levels are at or below the recommended levels for safe drinking. Keep this up!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Below you will find information and guidelines to help you stick to your current levels of &nbsp;safe, healthy drinking</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Heavy drinking in mid-life increases the risk of dementia later in life. Binge drinking (more than five half-pints of beer or a bottle of wine on one occasion) is associated with a higher risk of dementia. Heavy drinking can also damage your physical health and lead to heart disease, obesity, and some cancers.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="" src="images/riskfactors/alcool/chart.png" /></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>In Ireland, a standard drink has about 10&nbsp;grams of pure alcohol in it. In the UK, a standard drink &ndash; also called a unit of alcohol &ndash; has about 8&nbsp;grams of pure alcohol.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Remember</strong>, not all drinks measures are the same. What you get in a pub and what you pour for yourself could be very different.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>However, the overall amount of alcohol consumed by many people in Ireland puts them at risk of developing alcohol-related problems.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>These problems may be:</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Difficulty with memory</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Physical &ndash; such as heart disease</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Psychological &ndash; such as depression</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Social &ndash; such as acts of violence</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>What can I do?</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Cut down on alcohol if you are drinking more than the recommended limits</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Avoid binge drinking</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Take up social activities that do not include alcohol, such as going to the cinema, the theatre, or to a concert.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Know your measures!</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>If you are drinking more than the recommended limits to cope with stress, look for other ways to manage stress. You could take a yoga class or practise mindfulness or simply get outdoors. See the Mood page for more options.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you need help with your drinking, speak to your GP about where to get treatment locally.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Treatment may include:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Counselling</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Self-help groups, where people talk about their drinking problems in a supportive environment</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Medication, which can help to reduce cravings&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>', '<h1>Alcohol</h1>\r\n\r\n<h2 class="h-color">Room for improvement</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Your profile tells us that you drink more alcohol than the recommended limits. Making small changes to your drinking habits can have a positive effect on your brain health and your overall physical health.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Below you will find information and guidelines for safe, healthy drinking.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You will also find your personalised plan. This gives you a number of goals to choose from to help you drink less alcohol or stop drinking altogether.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Heavy drinking in mid-life increases the risk of dementia later in life. Binge drinking (more than five half-pints of beer or a bottle of wine on one occasion) is associated with a higher risk of dementia. Heavy drinking can also damage your physical health and lead to heart disease, obesity, and some cancers.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="" src="images/riskfactors/alcool/chart.png" /></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>In Ireland, a standard drink has about 10&nbsp;grams of pure alcohol in it. In the UK, a standard drink &ndash; also called a unit of alcohol &ndash; has about 8&nbsp;grams of pure alcohol.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Remember</strong>, not all drinks measures are the same. What you get in a pub and what you pour for yourself could be very different.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>However, the overall amount of alcohol consumed by many people in Ireland puts them at risk of developing alcohol-related problems.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>These problems may be:</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Difficulty with memory</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Physical &ndash; such as heart disease</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Psychological &ndash; such as depression</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Social &ndash; such as acts of violence</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>What can I do?</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Cut down on alcohol if you are drinking more than the recommended limits</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Avoid binge drinking</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Take up social activities that do not include alcohol, such as going to the cinema, the theatre, or to a concert.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Know your measures!</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>If you are drinking more than the recommended limits to cope with stress, look for other ways to manage stress. You could take a yoga class or practise mindfulness or simply get outdoors. See the Mood page for more options.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you need help with your drinking, speak to your GP about where to get treatment locally.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Treatment may include:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Counselling</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Self-help groups, where people talk about their drinking problems in a supportive environment</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Medication, which can help to reduce cravings&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>', '<h3>Further Supports:</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a href="http://www.yourdrinking.ie/">www.yourdrinking.ie</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Advice and information on safe drinking practices</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a href="http://www.alcoholicsanonymous.ie/">http://</a><a href="http://www.alcoholicsanonymous.ie/">www.alcoholicsanonymous.ie</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Offers information on where to access local groups who offer support to those who are experiencing problems due to their alcohol intake</p>'),
	(6, 'fr', 'Alcool', 'images/libra/drinking_amber.png', '<h1>Alcool</h1>\r\n\r\n<h2>Continuez comme &ccedil;a&nbsp;!</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Votre profile nous informe que votre consommation d&rsquo;alcool est inf&eacute;rieure ou &eacute;gale &agrave; ce qui est recommand&eacute; pour une consommation en toute s&eacute;curit&eacute;. Continuez comme &ccedil;a&nbsp;!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Ci-dessous vous trouverez les informations et des recommandations pour une consommation d&rsquo;alcool saine, en toute s&eacute;curit&eacute;.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Vous trouverez &eacute;galement votre programme personnalis&eacute;. Celui-ci vous propose un certain nombre d&rsquo;objectifs que vous pourrez choisir en vue de diminuer votre consommation d&rsquo;alcool ou arr&ecirc;ter d&rsquo;en boire compl&egrave;tement.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>L&rsquo;alcoolisme &agrave; l&rsquo;&acirc;ge m&ucirc;r accroit les risques de d&eacute;mence, qui surviendra plus tard. La consommation excessive d&rsquo;alcool (plus de cinq demis de bi&egrave;re ou une bouteille de vin lors d&rsquo;une seule occasion) est associ&eacute;e avec un risque plus &eacute;lev&eacute; de d&eacute;mence. De m&ecirc;me, cela peut nuire &agrave; votre sant&eacute; et conduire &agrave; des probl&egrave;mes cardiaques, &agrave; de l&rsquo;ob&eacute;sit&eacute; et &agrave; certains cancers.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="" src="images/riskfactors/alcool/french-chart.png" /></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>En France et Ireland, un verre normal servi dans un bar contient environ 10g d&rsquo;alcool pur. Au Royaume-Uni, il contient environ 8g d&rsquo;alcool pur.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Souvenez-vous bien</strong> que toutes les boissons ne sont pas dos&eacute;es de la m&ecirc;me mani&egrave;re. Ce qui est servi dans les bars et ce que vous vous servez chez vous n&rsquo;a souvent rien &agrave; voir.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Toutefois, la quantit&eacute; globale d&rsquo;alcool consomm&eacute;e par de nombreuses personnes en France leur fait courir le risque de d&eacute;velopper des probl&egrave;mes li&eacute;s &agrave; l&rsquo;alcool.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>&nbsp;</h3>\r\n\r\n<h3>Ces probl&egrave;mes sont&nbsp;:</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>- des difficult&eacute;s de m&eacute;moire</p>\r\n\r\n<p>- physiques, comme les probl&egrave;mes cardiaques par exemple</p>\r\n\r\n<p>- psychologiques, comme la d&eacute;pression</p>\r\n\r\n<p>- sociaux, comme des actes de violence</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Que dois-je faire&nbsp;?</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>- Vous pouvez r&eacute;duire votre consommation d&rsquo;alcool si elle est sup&eacute;rieure aux limites recommand&eacute;es.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>- &Eacute;vitez les beuveries</p>\r\n\r\n<p>- Participez &agrave; des activit&eacute;s sociales qui n&rsquo;incluent pas d&rsquo;alcool, comme aller au cin&eacute;ma, au th&eacute;&acirc;tre ou &agrave; un concert.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Prenez les bonnes mesures&nbsp;!</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Si vous buvez plus que les limites recommand&eacute;es pour surmonter votre stress, peut-&ecirc;tre pourriez vous trouver d&rsquo;autres moyens de le g&eacute;rer. Vous pourriez prendre des cours de yoga ou simplement faire un tour dehors. Pour en savoir plus, allez voir notre page sur l&rsquo;humeur.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Si vous avez besoin d&rsquo;aide par rapport &agrave; votre consommation d&rsquo;alcool, parlez en &agrave; votre m&eacute;decin traitant qui vous indiquera o&ugrave; trouver de l&rsquo;aide pr&egrave;s de chez vous.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Le traitement peut comprendre&nbsp;:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>- une psychoth&eacute;rapie</p>\r\n\r\n<p>- un groupe d&rsquo;entre-aide, o&ugrave; les personnes parlent de leurs probl&egrave;mes d&rsquo;alcool dans un environnement de soutien.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>- un traitement m&eacute;dical qui aide &agrave; r&eacute;duire le manque.</p>', '<h1>Alcool</h1>\r\n\r\n<h2 class="h-color">Une am&eacute;lioration est possible</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Votre profil nous informe que votre consommation d&rsquo;alcool d&eacute;passe les limites recommand&eacute;es. Pour la bonne sant&eacute; de votre cerveau et pour votre sant&eacute; globale, il serait b&eacute;n&eacute;fique d&rsquo;apporter quelques changements &agrave; votre habitude de boire.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Ci-dessous vous trouverez les informations et des recommandations pour une consommation d&rsquo;alcool saine, en toute s&eacute;curit&eacute;.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Vous trouverez &eacute;galement votre programme personnalis&eacute;. Celui-ci vous propose un certain nombre d&rsquo;objectifs que vous pourrez choisir en vue de diminuer votre consommation d&rsquo;alcool ou arr&ecirc;ter d&rsquo;en boire compl&egrave;tement.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>L&rsquo;alcoolisme &agrave; l&rsquo;&acirc;ge m&ucirc;r accroit les risques de d&eacute;mence, qui surviendra plus tard. La consommation excessive d&rsquo;alcool (plus de cinq demis de bi&egrave;re ou une bouteille de vin lors d&rsquo;une seule occasion) est associ&eacute;e avec un risque plus &eacute;lev&eacute; de d&eacute;mence. De m&ecirc;me, cela peut nuire &agrave; votre sant&eacute; et conduire &agrave; des probl&egrave;mes cardiaques, &agrave; de l&rsquo;ob&eacute;sit&eacute; et &agrave; certains cancers.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="" src="images/riskfactors/alcool/french-chart.png" /></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>En France et Ireland, un verre normal servi dans un bar contient environ 10g d&rsquo;alcool pur. Au Royaume-Uni, il contient environ 8g d&rsquo;alcool pur.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Souvenez-vous bien</strong> que toutes les boissons ne sont pas dos&eacute;es de la m&ecirc;me mani&egrave;re. Ce qui est servi dans les bars et ce que vous vous servez chez vous n&rsquo;a souvent rien &agrave; voir.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Toutefois, la quantit&eacute; globale d&rsquo;alcool consomm&eacute;e par de nombreuses personnes en France leur fait courir le risque de d&eacute;velopper des probl&egrave;mes li&eacute;s &agrave; l&rsquo;alcool.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>&nbsp;</h3>\r\n\r\n<h3>Ces probl&egrave;mes sont&nbsp;:</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>- des difficult&eacute;s de m&eacute;moire</p>\r\n\r\n<p>- physiques, comme les probl&egrave;mes cardiaques par exemple</p>\r\n\r\n<p>- psychologiques, comme la d&eacute;pression</p>\r\n\r\n<p>- sociaux, comme des actes de violence</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Que dois-je faire&nbsp;?</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>- Vous pouvez r&eacute;duire votre consommation d&rsquo;alcool si elle est sup&eacute;rieure aux limites recommand&eacute;es.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>- &Eacute;vitez les beuveries</p>\r\n\r\n<p>- Participez &agrave; des activit&eacute;s sociales qui n&rsquo;incluent pas d&rsquo;alcool, comme aller au cin&eacute;ma, au th&eacute;&acirc;tre ou &agrave; un concert.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Prenez les bonnes mesures&nbsp;!</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Si vous buvez plus que les limites recommand&eacute;es pour surmonter votre stress, peut-&ecirc;tre pourriez vous trouver d&rsquo;autres moyens de le g&eacute;rer. Vous pourriez prendre des cours de yoga ou simplement faire un tour dehors. Pour en savoir plus, allez voir notre page sur l&rsquo;humeur.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Si vous avez besoin d&rsquo;aide par rapport &agrave; votre consommation d&rsquo;alcool, parlez en &agrave; votre m&eacute;decin traitant qui vous indiquera o&ugrave; trouver de l&rsquo;aide pr&egrave;s de chez vous.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Le traitement peut comprendre&nbsp;:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>- une psychoth&eacute;rapie</p>\r\n\r\n<p>- un groupe d&rsquo;entre-aide, o&ugrave; les personnes parlent de leurs probl&egrave;mes d&rsquo;alcool dans un environnement de soutien.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>- un traitement m&eacute;dical qui aide &agrave; r&eacute;duire le manque.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', ' '),
	(6, 'sc', 'Drinking', 'images/libra/drinking_amber.png', '<h1>Alcohol</h1>\r\n\r\n<h2 class="h-color">Keep this up!</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Your profile tells us that your alcohol levels are at or below the recommended levels for safe drinking. Keep this up!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Below you will find information and guidelines to help you stick to your current levels of &nbsp;safe, healthy drinking</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Heavy drinking in mid-life increases the risk of dementia later in life. Binge drinking (more than five half-pints of beer or a bottle of wine on one occasion) is associated with a higher risk of dementia. Heavy drinking can also damage your physical health and lead to heart disease, obesity, and some cancers.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="" src="images/riskfactors/alcool/chart.png" /></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>In Ireland, a standard drink has about 10&nbsp;grams of pure alcohol in it. In the UK, a standard drink &ndash; also called a unit of alcohol &ndash; has about 8&nbsp;grams of pure alcohol.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Remember</strong>, not all drinks measures are the same. What you get in a pub and what you pour for yourself could be very different.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>However, the overall amount of alcohol consumed by many people in Ireland puts them at risk of developing alcohol-related problems.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>These problems may be:</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Difficulty with memory</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Physical &ndash; such as heart disease</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Psychological &ndash; such as depression</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Social &ndash; such as acts of violence</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>What can I do?</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Cut down on alcohol if you are drinking more than the recommended limits</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Avoid binge drinking</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Take up social activities that do not include alcohol, such as going to the cinema, the theatre, or to a concert.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Know your measures!</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>If you are drinking more than the recommended limits to cope with stress, look for other ways to manage stress. You could take a yoga class or practise mindfulness or simply get outdoors. See the Mood page for more options.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you need help with your drinking, speak to your GP about where to get treatment locally.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Treatment may include:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Counselling</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Self-help groups, where people talk about their drinking problems in a supportive environment</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Medication, which can help to reduce cravings&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>', '<h1>Alcohol</h1>\r\n\r\n<h2 class="h-color">Room for improvement</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Your profile tells us that you drink more alcohol than the recommended limits. Making small changes to your drinking habits can have a positive effect on your brain health and your overall physical health.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Below you will find information and guidelines for safe, healthy drinking.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You will also find your personalised plan. This gives you a number of goals to choose from to help you drink less alcohol or stop drinking altogether.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Heavy drinking in mid-life increases the risk of dementia later in life. Binge drinking (more than five half-pints of beer or a bottle of wine on one occasion) is associated with a higher risk of dementia. Heavy drinking can also damage your physical health and lead to heart disease, obesity, and some cancers.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="" src="images/riskfactors/alcool/chart.png" /></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>In Ireland, a standard drink has about 10&nbsp;grams of pure alcohol in it. In the UK, a standard drink &ndash; also called a unit of alcohol &ndash; has about 8&nbsp;grams of pure alcohol.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Remember</strong>, not all drinks measures are the same. What you get in a pub and what you pour for yourself could be very different.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>However, the overall amount of alcohol consumed by many people in Ireland puts them at risk of developing alcohol-related problems.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>These problems may be:</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Difficulty with memory</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Physical &ndash; such as heart disease</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Psychological &ndash; such as depression</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Social &ndash; such as acts of violence</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>What can I do?</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Cut down on alcohol if you are drinking more than the recommended limits</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Avoid binge drinking</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Take up social activities that do not include alcohol, such as going to the cinema, the theatre, or to a concert.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Know your measures!</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>If you are drinking more than the recommended limits to cope with stress, look for other ways to manage stress. You could take a yoga class or practise mindfulness or simply get outdoors. See the Mood page for more options.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you need help with your drinking, speak to your GP about where to get treatment locally.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Treatment may include:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Counselling</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Self-help groups, where people talk about their drinking problems in a supportive environment</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Medication, which can help to reduce cravings&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>', '<h3>Further Supports:</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>NHS information on drinking and alcohol:</p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href="http://www.nhs.uk/livewell/alcohol/Pages/Alcoholhome.aspx">http://www.nhs.uk/livewell/alcohol/Pages/Alcoholhome.aspx</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Drinkaware is an independent UK-wide charity that promotes responsible drinking. The web site includes alcohol unit calculator and drinking self-assessment tool:</p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href="https://www.drinkaware.co.uk/">https://www.drinkaware.co.uk/</a></p>'),
	(7, 'en', 'Obesity', 'images/libra/obesity_amber.png', '<h1>Obesity</h1>\r\n\r\n<h2 class="h-color">Keep this up!</h2>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Your profile tells us that your BMI is less than 30. &nbsp;This is important as a healthy weight is good for your overall brain health. Keep this up!</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>What we know</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Obesity in middle age could increase the risk of dementia later in life.</li>\r\n	<li>Studies on <strong><a class="inlinePopup" href="#inlineCognitive">cognitive function</a></strong> and body mass index (<a href="http://www.nhs.uk/Tools/Pages/Healthyweightcalculator.aspx">Calculate your BMI</a>) found that obese people have more trouble on memory and reasoning tests.</li>\r\n	<li>High blood pressure is often associated with obesity and could increase the risk of dementia later in life.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>A quick guide to obesity</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>A person who is obese has so much excess body fat that his or her health may suffer. Obesity is a medical condition.</li>\r\n	<li>Body mass index (<a href="http://www.nhs.uk/Tools/Pages/Healthyweightcalculator.aspx">BMI</a>) is a formula used to check whether a person is at a healthy weight for their height. A person is considered obese if they have a BMI of 30 or more.</li>\r\n	<li>Obesity has many causes and is not just about eating too much food.</li>\r\n	<li>Many of us are less physically active than our parents or grandparents were. Instead of walking everywhere, we travel in cars or on public transport. Many of us also have jobs that require us to sit for most of the day.</li>\r\n	<li>Lowering your BMI to a healthy level is not only good for your physical health but also improves your brain health.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="" src="images/riskfactors/diet/goal.jpg" /></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>What can I do?</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>To lose weight, you need to reduce the number of <a class="inlinePopup" href="#inlineCalorie">calories</a> you eat and drink every day and increase the amount of exercise you get.</li>\r\n	<li>If you are not physically active, you should ask your GP about the type of exercise you should do and how much, depending on how fit you are.</li>\r\n	<li>You can start by spending less time sitting at your computer or in front of the television.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>Take more exercise!</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Build up slowly. Choose physical activities that you enjoy. You&rsquo;ll be more likely to keep doing them then.</li>\r\n	<li>Start with activities that you can fit into your everyday life, like walking, gardening or taking the stairs instead of the lift</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="" src="images/riskfactors/obesity/walk.png" /></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Be realistic</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Set realistic weight loss goals.</li>\r\n	<li>Keep a food diary. This is a good way to keep track of how many <a class="inlinePopup" href="#inlineCalorie">calories</a> you are eating.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Join a local slimming club if you think this may help you.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>With support, we can make simple changes that help us to feel better physically and mentally and to maintain good brain health.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>If you choose food from the Mediterranean Diet, eat more fruit and vegetables every day, and use olive oil instead of butter or margarine, your diet and your brain health will improve.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div style="display:none;">\r\n<div id="inlineCognitive" style="padding:10px; background:#fff;">\r\n<p>Cognitive function refers to memory, the ability to learn new information, process thoughts, speech and reading comprehension.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div id="inlineCalorie" style="padding:10px; background:#fff;">\r\n<p>A calorie is a unit of energy. It describes how much energy your body gets from eating or drinking. Most food and drinks contain calories. If you eat or drink more calories than you need, the leftover calories are converted to fat. If you only eat and drink the recommended daily number of calories, and if you also take enough exercise, you will stay within a healthy weight range. Being active is important because physical activity burns calories.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>', '<h1>Obesity</h1>\r\n\r\n<h2 class="h-color">Room for improvement</h2>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Your profile tells us that your BMI is &hellip;over 30&hellip;.. <a href="http://www.nhs.uk/Tools/Pages/Healthyweightcalculator.aspx">What is BMI and obesity?</a> There is room to improve your diet and your level of physical activity. Just a few small changes can lower your BMI, improve your brain health, and reduce your risk of dementia later in life.</li>\r\n	<li>BMI stands for body mass index. It is a formula used to check whether a person is underweight, overweight or at a healthy weight. The formula divides your weight by the square of your height to get a BMI score. Anyone with a BMI score of between 18.5 to 25 is considered a healthy weight, while 25 to 30 is overweight. A score of more than 30 is described as obese. <a href="http://www.nhs.uk/Tools/Pages/Healthyweightcalculator.aspx">Click here to calculate your BMI</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>What we know</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Obesity in middle age could increase the risk of dementia later in life.</li>\r\n	<li>Studies on <strong><a class="inlinePopup" href="#inlineCognitive">cognitive function</a></strong> and body mass index (<a href="http://www.nhs.uk/Tools/Pages/Healthyweightcalculator.aspx">BMI</a>) found that obese people have more trouble on memory and reasoning tests.</li>\r\n	<li>High blood pressure is often associated with obesity and could increase the risk of dementia later in life.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>A quick guide to obesity</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>A person who is obese has so much excess body fat that his or her health may suffer. Obesity is a medical condition.</li>\r\n	<li>Body mass index (<a href="http://www.nhs.uk/Tools/Pages/Healthyweightcalculator.aspx">BMI</a>) is a formula used to check whether a person is at a healthy weight for their height. A person is considered obese if they have a BMI of 30 or more.</li>\r\n	<li>Obesity has many causes and is not just about eating too much food.</li>\r\n	<li>Many of us are less physically active than our parents or grandparents were. Instead of walking everywhere, we travel in cars or on public transport. Many of us also have jobs that require us to sit for most of the day.</li>\r\n	<li>Lowering your BMI to a healthy level is not only good for your physical health but also improves your brain health.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="" src="images/riskfactors/diet/goal.jpg" /></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>What can I do?</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>To lose weight, you need to reduce the number of <a class="inlinePopup" href="#inlineCalorie">calories</a> you eat and drink every day and increase the amount of exercise you get.</li>\r\n	<li>If you are not physically active, you should ask your GP about the type of exercise you should do and how much, depending on how fit you are.</li>\r\n	<li>You can start by spending less time sitting at your computer or in front of the television.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>Take more exercise!</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Build up slowly. Choose physical activities that you enjoy. You&rsquo;ll be more likely to keep doing them then.</li>\r\n	<li>Start with activities that you can fit into your everyday life, like walking, gardening or taking the stairs instead of the lift</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="" src="images/riskfactors/obesity/walk.png" /></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Be realistic</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Set realistic weight loss goals.</li>\r\n	<li>Keep a food diary. This is a good way to keep track of how many <a class="inlinePopup" href="#inlineCalorie">calories</a> you are eating.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Join a local slimming club if you think this may help you.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>With support, we can make simple changes that help us to feel better physically and mentally and to maintain good brain health.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>How does my plan work?</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>The plan is meant to help you lose weight. A weight loss of 5%-10% will be good for your heart and your brain health.</li>\r\n	<li>Below are three goals that can help you lose weight by changing your diet and by exercising.</li>\r\n	<li>Remember, if you are not enjoying the changes to your diet or exercise habits, you will find it harder to keep going.&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;Choose one of the goals below. If you find it hard to fit these changes into your lifestyle, then come back and choose another goal!</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Choosing one of the goals above will help you lose weight and improve your BMI. It may take some time to get your BMI below 30. But remember that making simple changes to your diet and taking more exercise may help you to improve your overall brain health score. The plan is meant to help you make positive changes to your diet and exercise habits.</li>\r\n	<li>Choosing food from the Mediterranean Diet is a good way to improve your diet and, in turn, your brain health. Your brain will also benefit if you eat more fruit and vegetables every day and use olive oil instead of butter or margarine.</li>\r\n	<li>If you make simple changes to your diet, take more exercise, and choose one of the goals above, you will improve your overall brain health score.</li>\r\n	<li>If you choose food from the Mediterranean Diet, eat more fruit and vegetables every day, and use olive oil instead of butter or margarine, your diet and your brain health will improve.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div style="display:none;">\r\n<div id="inlineCognitive" style="padding:10px; background:#fff;">\r\n<p>Cognitive function refers to memory, the ability to learn new information, process thoughts, speech and reading comprehension.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div id="inlineCalorie" style="padding:10px; background:#fff;">\r\n<p>A calorie is a unit of energy. It describes how much energy your body gets from eating or drinking. Most food and drinks contain calories. If you eat or drink more calories than you need, the leftover calories are converted to fat. If you only eat and drink the recommended daily number of calories, and if you also take enough exercise, you will stay within a healthy weight range. Being active is important because physical activity burns calories.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n', '<h3>Other Supports</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><a href="http://www.hse.ie/phew">www.hse.ie/phew</a></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>This is a 6 week programme for healthy eating and weight management designed for overweight individuals</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><a href="http://www.getirelandactive.ie">www.getirelandactive.ie</a></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>This website highlights the importance of physical activity to the health of Irish people, provides information, recommendations and support for people of all ages and abilities to get active</li>\r\n</ul>'),
	(7, 'fr', 'Obsit', 'images/libra/obesity_amber.png', '<h1>Ob&eacute;sit&eacute;</h1>\r\n\r\n<h2>Continuez comme &ccedil;a&nbsp;!</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Votre profil nous informe que votre IMC est inf&eacute;rieur &agrave; 30. C&rsquo;est important, car un poids sain est b&eacute;n&eacute;fique pour votre sant&eacute; c&eacute;r&eacute;brale g&eacute;n&eacute;rale. Continuez comme &ccedil;a&nbsp;!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Ce que nous savons</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>L&rsquo;ob&eacute;sit&eacute; durant l&rsquo;&acirc;ge adulte est susceptible d&rsquo;augmenter le risqu&eacute; de d&eacute;mence plus tard dans la vie.</li>\r\n	<li>Les &eacute;tudes sur les <ins>fonctions cognitives</ins> et l&rsquo;indice de masse corporelle (<a href="http://www.obesite-sante.com/comprendre_l_obesite/obesite_et_surpoids/calcul_du_poids_ideal.shtml">IMC</a>) ont observ&eacute; que les personnes ob&egrave;ses ont davantage de difficult&eacute;s aux tests de m&eacute;moire et de raisonnement.</li>\r\n	<li>Une tension art&eacute;rielle &eacute;lev&eacute;e est souvent associ&eacute;e &agrave; l&rsquo;ob&eacute;sit&eacute;, et peut augmenter le risque de d&eacute;mence avec l&rsquo;avanc&eacute;e en &acirc;ge.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>Un guide rapide concernant l&rsquo;ob&eacute;sit&eacute;</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Une personne ob&egrave;se a tellement de graisse corporelle en exc&egrave;s que sa sant&eacute; peut en souffrir. L&rsquo;ob&eacute;sit&eacute; est une condition m&eacute;dicale.</li>\r\n	<li>L&rsquo;indice de masse corporelle (<a href="http://www.obesite-sante.com/comprendre_l_obesite/obesite_et_surpoids/calcul_du_poids_ideal.shtml">IMC</a>)&nbsp; est une formule utilis&eacute;e pour v&eacute;rifier si une personne a un poids sain en fonction de sa taille. Une personne est consid&eacute;r&eacute;e ob&egrave;se si elle a un IMC sup&eacute;rieur ou &eacute;gal &agrave; 30.</li>\r\n	<li>L&rsquo;ob&eacute;sit&eacute; a de nombreuses causes, et ne r&eacute;sulte pas seulement de manger trop de nourriture.</li>\r\n	<li>Beaucoup d&rsquo;entre nous sont moins actifs physiquement que nos parents ou grands-parents l&rsquo;&eacute;taient. Plut&ocirc;t que de marcher en toute occasion, nous nous d&eacute;pla&ccedil;ons en voiture ou avec les transports publics. Beaucoup de nous avons &eacute;galement un travail qui n&eacute;cessite que nous soyons assis toute la journ&eacute;e.</li>\r\n	<li>R&eacute;duire votre IMC &agrave; un niveau sain n&rsquo;est pas seulement bon pour votre sant&eacute; physique, mais aussi pour am&eacute;liorer votre sant&eacute; c&eacute;r&eacute;brale.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="" src="images/riskfactors/diet/goal.jpg" /></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Que puis-je faire&nbsp;?</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Pour perdre du poids, vous devez r&eacute;duire le nombre de <ins>calories</ins> que vous mangez et buvez chaque jour, et augmenter la quantit&eacute; d&rsquo;exercice que vous effectuez.</li>\r\n	<li>Si vous n&rsquo;&ecirc;tes pas physiquement actif, vous pourriez demander &agrave; votre m&eacute;decin traitant de vous renseigner sur les types d&rsquo;exercices que vous pourriez faire et en quelle quantit&eacute;, en fonction de votre forme.</li>\r\n	<li>Vous pouvez commencer par passer moins de temps assis devant votre ordinateur ou devant la t&eacute;l&eacute;vision.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>Faites plus d&rsquo;exercice&nbsp;!</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Progressez doucement. Choisissez des activit&eacute;s physiques qui vous plaisent. Vous serez alors plus enclin &agrave; continuer &agrave; les faire.</li>\r\n	<li>Commencez avec des activit&eacute;s que vous pouvez int&eacute;grer &agrave; votre vie quotidienne, comme marcher, jardiner, ou prendre les escaliers plut&ocirc;t que l&rsquo;ascenseur.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="" src="images/riskfactors/obesity/walk.png" /></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Soyez r&eacute;aliste</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Choisissez des objectifs r&eacute;alistes pour votre perte de poids.</li>\r\n	<li>Gardez un journal alimentaire. C&rsquo;est une bonne fa&ccedil;on de garder une trace sur la quantit&eacute; de <ins>calories</ins> que vous mangez.</li>\r\n	<li>Rejoignez un club de natation proche de chez vous si vous pensez que cela peut vous aider.</li>\r\n	<li>Avec de l&rsquo;aide, nous pouvons mettre en place des changements simples pour nous aider &agrave; nous sentir mieux physiquement et mentalement, et &agrave; maintenir une bonne sant&eacute; c&eacute;r&eacute;brale.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>Comment fonctionne mon plan?</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Le plan est destin&eacute; &agrave; vous aider &agrave; perdre du poids. Une perte de poids de 5 &agrave; 10% sera b&eacute;n&eacute;fique pour votre sant&eacute; cardiaque et c&eacute;r&eacute;brale.</li>\r\n	<li>Ci-dessous sont expos&eacute;s trois objectifs qui peuvent vous aider &agrave; perdre du poids, en changeant votre alimentation ou en faisant de l&rsquo;exercice.</li>\r\n	<li>Rappelez-vous que si vous n&rsquo;appr&eacute;ciez pas les changements dans votre alimentation ou votre activit&eacute; physique, vous trouverez &ccedil;a plus difficile de les maintenir sur la dur&eacute;e.</li>\r\n	<li>Choisissez l&rsquo;un des objectifs ci-dessous. Si vous trouvez difficile d&rsquo;appliquer ces changement dans votre mode de vie, alors revenez ici et choisissez un nouvel objectif&nbsp;!</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Choisir l&rsquo;un des objectifs ci-dessus vous aidera &agrave; perdre du poids et &agrave; am&eacute;liorer votre IMC. Cela pourra prendre du temps pour amener votre IMC en-dessous de 30. Mais rappelez-vous que faire des changements simples dans votre alimentation et faire plus d&rsquo;exercice peut vous aider &agrave; am&eacute;liorer votre score g&eacute;n&eacute;ral de sant&eacute; c&eacute;r&eacute;brale. Votre plan est l&agrave; pour vous aider &agrave; mettre en place des changements positifs dans votre alimentation et votre activit&eacute; physique.</li>\r\n	<li>Choisir votre nourriture d&rsquo;apr&egrave;s un r&eacute;gime alimentaire m&eacute;diterran&eacute;en est une bonne fa&ccedil;on d&rsquo;am&eacute;liorer votre alimentation et, en retour, votre sant&eacute; c&eacute;r&eacute;brale. Des b&eacute;n&eacute;fices pour votre cerveau se produiront &eacute;galement si vous mangez plus de fruits et de l&eacute;gumes chaque jour, et que vous utilisez de l&rsquo;huile d&rsquo;olive &agrave; la place du beurre ou de la margarine.</li>\r\n	<li>Si vous faites des changements simples &agrave; votre alimentation, que vous faites plus d&rsquo;exercice physique, et que vous choisissez l&rsquo;un des objectifs ci-dessus, vous am&eacute;liorerez votre score g&eacute;n&eacute;ral de sant&eacute; c&eacute;r&eacute;brale.</li>\r\n	<li>Si vous choisissez votre nourriture d&rsquo;apr&egrave;s un r&eacute;gime alimentaire m&eacute;diterran&eacute;en, mangez plus de fruits et l&eacute;gumes chaque jour, et que vous utilisez de l&rsquo;huile d&rsquo;olive &agrave; la place du beurre et de la margarine, votre alimentation et votre sant&eacute; c&eacute;r&eacute;brale s&rsquo;am&eacute;lioreront.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div style="display:none;">\r\n<div id="inlineCognitive" style="padding:10px; background:#fff;">\r\n<p>Le fonctionnement cognitif se rapporte &agrave; la m&eacute;moire, la capacit&eacute; &agrave; apprendre de nouvelles informations, les capacit&eacute;s de r&eacute;flexion, et la compr&eacute;hension orale et &eacute;crite.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div id="inlineCalorie" style="padding:10px; background:#fff;">\r\n<p>Une calorie est une unit&eacute; d&rsquo;&eacute;nergie. Elle d&eacute;crit la quantit&eacute; d&rsquo;&eacute;nergie que votre corps obtient par la nourriture et les boissons. La plupart des nourritures et des boissons contiennent des calories. Si vous mangez ou buvez plus de calories que ce dont vous avez besoin, les calories en surplus sont converties en graisse. Si vous mangez et buvez uniquement la quantit&eacute; journali&egrave;re recommand&eacute;e de calories, et si vous faites &eacute;galement de l&rsquo;exercice, vous garderez un poids sain. Etre actif est &eacute;galement important, car l&rsquo;activit&eacute; physique permet de br&ucirc;ler des calories.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>', '<h1>Ob&eacute;sit&eacute;</h1>\r\n\r\n<h2>Une am&eacute;lioration est possible</h2>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Votre profil nous informe que votre IMC est au-del&agrave; de 30. <a href="http://www.obesite-sante.com/comprendre_l_obesite/obesite_et_surpoids/calcul_du_poids_ideal.shtml">Qu&rsquo;est-ce que l&rsquo;IMC et l&rsquo;ob&eacute;sit&eacute;</a>? Il est vous est possible d&rsquo;am&eacute;liorer votre r&eacute;gime alimentaire et votre niveau d&rsquo;activit&eacute; physique. Seulement quelques petits changements pourraient r&eacute;duire votre IMC, am&eacute;liorer votre sant&eacute; c&eacute;r&eacute;brale, et r&eacute;duire votre risque de d&eacute;mence en vieillissant.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>IMC signifie Indice de Masse Corpoorelle. Il s&rsquo;agit d&rsquo;une formule utilis&eacute;e pour v&eacute;rifier si une personne est en sous-poids, en surpoids, ou a un poids normal. La formule divise votre poids par votre taille au carr&eacute;, pour fournir un score IMC. Une personne avec un IMC compris entre 18,5 et 25 est consid&eacute;r&eacute;e comme ayant un poids normal, alors qu&rsquo;un IMC entre 25 et 30 indique un surpoids. Un score de plus de 30 indique une ob&eacute;sit&eacute;. <a href="http://www.obesite-sante.com/comprendre_l_obesite/obesite_et_surpoids/calcul_du_poids_ideal.shtml">Cliquez ici pour calculer votre IMC</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Ce que nous savons</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>L&rsquo;ob&eacute;sit&eacute; durant l&rsquo;&acirc;ge adulte est susceptible d&rsquo;augmenter le risqu&eacute; de d&eacute;mence plus tard dans la vie.</li>\r\n	<li>Les &eacute;tudes sur les <ins>fonctions cognitives</ins> et l&rsquo;indice de masse corporelle (<a href="http://www.obesite-sante.com/comprendre_l_obesite/obesite_et_surpoids/calcul_du_poids_ideal.shtml">IMC</a>) ont observ&eacute; que les personnes ob&egrave;ses ont davantage de difficult&eacute;s aux tests de m&eacute;moire et de raisonnement.</li>\r\n	<li>Une tension art&eacute;rielle &eacute;lev&eacute;e est souvent associ&eacute;e &agrave; l&rsquo;ob&eacute;sit&eacute;, et peut augmenter le risque de d&eacute;mence avec l&rsquo;avanc&eacute;e en &acirc;ge.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>Un guide rapide concernant l&rsquo;ob&eacute;sit&eacute;</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Une personne ob&egrave;se a tellement de graisse corporelle en exc&egrave;s que sa sant&eacute; peut en souffrir. L&rsquo;ob&eacute;sit&eacute; est une condition m&eacute;dicale.</li>\r\n	<li>L&rsquo;indice de masse corporelle (<a href="http://www.obesite-sante.com/comprendre_l_obesite/obesite_et_surpoids/calcul_du_poids_ideal.shtml">IMC</a>)&nbsp; est une formule utilis&eacute;e pour v&eacute;rifier si une personne a un poids sain en fonction de sa taille. Une personne est consid&eacute;r&eacute;e ob&egrave;se si elle a un IMC sup&eacute;rieur ou &eacute;gal &agrave; 30.</li>\r\n	<li>L&rsquo;ob&eacute;sit&eacute; a de nombreuses causes, et ne r&eacute;sulte pas seulement de manger trop de nourriture.</li>\r\n	<li>Beaucoup d&rsquo;entre nous sont moins actifs physiquement que nos parents ou grands-parents l&rsquo;&eacute;taient. Plut&ocirc;t que de marcher en toute occasion, nous nous d&eacute;pla&ccedil;ons en voiture ou avec les transports publics. Beaucoup de nous avons &eacute;galement un travail qui n&eacute;cessite que nous soyons assis toute la journ&eacute;e.</li>\r\n	<li>R&eacute;duire votre IMC &agrave; un niveau sain n&rsquo;est pas seulement bon pour votre sant&eacute; physique, mais aussi pour am&eacute;liorer votre sant&eacute; c&eacute;r&eacute;brale.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="" src="images/riskfactors/diet/goal.jpg" /></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Que puis-je faire&nbsp;?</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Pour perdre du poids, vous devez r&eacute;duire le nombre de <ins>calories</ins> que vous mangez et buvez chaque jour, et augmenter la quantit&eacute; d&rsquo;exercice que vous effectuez.</li>\r\n	<li>Si vous n&rsquo;&ecirc;tes pas physiquement actif, vous pourriez demander &agrave; votre m&eacute;decin traitant de vous renseigner sur les types d&rsquo;exercices que vous pourriez faire et en quelle quantit&eacute;, en fonction de votre forme.</li>\r\n	<li>Vous pouvez commencer par passer moins de temps assis devant votre ordinateur ou devant la t&eacute;l&eacute;vision.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>Faites plus d&rsquo;exercice&nbsp;!</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Progressez doucement. Choisissez des activit&eacute;s physiques qui vous plaisent. Vous serez alors plus enclin &agrave; continuer &agrave; les faire.</li>\r\n	<li>Commencez avec des activit&eacute;s que vous pouvez int&eacute;grer &agrave; votre vie quotidienne, comme marcher, jardiner, ou prendre les escaliers plut&ocirc;t que l&rsquo;ascenseur.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="" src="images/riskfactors/obesity/walk.png" /></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Soyez r&eacute;aliste</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Choisissez des objectifs r&eacute;alistes pour votre perte de poids.</li>\r\n	<li>Gardez un journal alimentaire. C&rsquo;est une bonne fa&ccedil;on de garder une trace sur la quantit&eacute; de <ins>calories</ins> que vous mangez.</li>\r\n	<li>Rejoignez un club de natation proche de chez vous si vous pensez que cela peut vous aider.</li>\r\n	<li>Avec de l&rsquo;aide, nous pouvons mettre en place des changements simples pour nous aider &agrave; nous sentir mieux physiquement et mentalement, et &agrave; maintenir une bonne sant&eacute; c&eacute;r&eacute;brale.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>Comment fonctionne mon plan?</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Le plan est destin&eacute; &agrave; vous aider &agrave; perdre du poids. Une perte de poids de 5 &agrave; 10% sera b&eacute;n&eacute;fique pour votre sant&eacute; cardiaque et c&eacute;r&eacute;brale.</li>\r\n	<li>Ci-dessous sont expos&eacute;s trois objectifs qui peuvent vous aider &agrave; perdre du poids, en changeant votre alimentation ou en faisant de l&rsquo;exercice.</li>\r\n	<li>Rappelez-vous que si vous n&rsquo;appr&eacute;ciez pas les changements dans votre alimentation ou votre activit&eacute; physique, vous trouverez &ccedil;a plus difficile de les maintenir sur la dur&eacute;e.</li>\r\n	<li>Choisissez l&rsquo;un des objectifs ci-dessous. Si vous trouvez difficile d&rsquo;appliquer ces changement dans votre mode de vie, alors revenez ici et choisissez un nouvel objectif&nbsp;!</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Choisir l&rsquo;un des objectifs ci-dessus vous aidera &agrave; perdre du poids et &agrave; am&eacute;liorer votre IMC. Cela pourra prendre du temps pour amener votre IMC en-dessous de 30. Mais rappelez-vous que faire des changements simples dans votre alimentation et faire plus d&rsquo;exercice peut vous aider &agrave; am&eacute;liorer votre score g&eacute;n&eacute;ral de sant&eacute; c&eacute;r&eacute;brale. Votre plan est l&agrave; pour vous aider &agrave; mettre en place des changements positifs dans votre alimentation et votre activit&eacute; physique.</li>\r\n	<li>Choisir votre nourriture d&rsquo;apr&egrave;s un r&eacute;gime alimentaire m&eacute;diterran&eacute;en est une bonne fa&ccedil;on d&rsquo;am&eacute;liorer votre alimentation et, en retour, votre sant&eacute; c&eacute;r&eacute;brale. Des b&eacute;n&eacute;fices pour votre cerveau se produiront &eacute;galement si vous mangez plus de fruits et de l&eacute;gumes chaque jour, et que vous utilisez de l&rsquo;huile d&rsquo;olive &agrave; la place du beurre ou de la margarine.</li>\r\n	<li>Si vous faites des changements simples &agrave; votre alimentation, que vous faites plus d&rsquo;exercice physique, et que vous choisissez l&rsquo;un des objectifs ci-dessus, vous am&eacute;liorerez votre score g&eacute;n&eacute;ral de sant&eacute; c&eacute;r&eacute;brale.</li>\r\n	<li>Si vous choisissez votre nourriture d&rsquo;apr&egrave;s un r&eacute;gime alimentaire m&eacute;diterran&eacute;en, mangez plus de fruits et l&eacute;gumes chaque jour, et que vous utilisez de l&rsquo;huile d&rsquo;olive &agrave; la place du beurre et de la margarine, votre alimentation et votre sant&eacute; c&eacute;r&eacute;brale s&rsquo;am&eacute;lioreront.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div style="display:none;">\r\n<div id="inlineCognitive" style="padding:10px; background:#fff;">\r\n<p>Le fonctionnement cognitif se rapporte &agrave; la m&eacute;moire, la capacit&eacute; &agrave; apprendre de nouvelles informations, les capacit&eacute;s de r&eacute;flexion, et la compr&eacute;hension orale et &eacute;crite.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div id="inlineCalorie" style="padding:10px; background:#fff;">\r\n<p>Une calorie est une unit&eacute; d&rsquo;&eacute;nergie. Elle d&eacute;crit la quantit&eacute; d&rsquo;&eacute;nergie que votre corps obtient par la nourriture et les boissons. La plupart des nourritures et des boissons contiennent des calories. Si vous mangez ou buvez plus de calories que ce dont vous avez besoin, les calories en surplus sont converties en graisse. Si vous mangez et buvez uniquement la quantit&eacute; journali&egrave;re recommand&eacute;e de calories, et si vous faites &eacute;galement de l&rsquo;exercice, vous garderez un poids sain. Etre actif est &eacute;galement important, car l&rsquo;activit&eacute; physique permet de br&ucirc;ler des calories.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n', ' '),
	(7, 'sc', 'Obesity', 'images/libra/obesity_amber.png', '<h1>Obesity</h1>\r\n\r\n<h2 class="h-color">Keep this up!</h2>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Your profile tells us that your BMI is less than 30. &nbsp;This is important as a healthy weight is good for your overall brain health. Keep this up!</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>What we know</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Obesity in middle age could increase the risk of dementia later in life.</li>\r\n	<li>Studies on <strong><a class="inlinePopup" href="#inlineCognitive">cognitive function</a></strong> and body mass index (<a href="http://www.nhs.uk/Tools/Pages/Healthyweightcalculator.aspx">Calculate your BMI</a>) found that obese people have more trouble on memory and reasoning tests.</li>\r\n	<li>High blood pressure is often associated with obesity and could increase the risk of dementia later in life.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>A quick guide to obesity</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>A person who is obese has so much excess body fat that his or her health may suffer. Obesity is a medical condition.</li>\r\n	<li>Body mass index (<a href="http://www.nhs.uk/Tools/Pages/Healthyweightcalculator.aspx">BMI</a>) is a formula used to check whether a person is at a healthy weight for their height. A person is considered obese if they have a BMI of 30 or more.</li>\r\n	<li>Obesity has many causes and is not just about eating too much food.</li>\r\n	<li>Many of us are less physically active than our parents or grandparents were. Instead of walking everywhere, we travel in cars or on public transport. Many of us also have jobs that require us to sit for most of the day.</li>\r\n	<li>Lowering your BMI to a healthy level is not only good for your physical health but also improves your brain health.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="" src="images/riskfactors/diet/goal.jpg" /></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>What can I do?</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>To lose weight, you need to reduce the number of <a class="inlinePopup" href="#inlineCalorie">calories</a> you eat and drink every day and increase the amount of exercise you get.</li>\r\n	<li>If you are not physically active, you should ask your GP about the type of exercise you should do and how much, depending on how fit you are.</li>\r\n	<li>You can start by spending less time sitting at your computer or in front of the television.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>Take more exercise!</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Build up slowly. Choose physical activities that you enjoy. You&rsquo;ll be more likely to keep doing them then.</li>\r\n	<li>Start with activities that you can fit into your everyday life, like walking, gardening or taking the stairs instead of the lift</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="" src="images/riskfactors/obesity/walk.png" /></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Be realistic</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Set realistic weight loss goals.</li>\r\n	<li>Keep a food diary. This is a good way to keep track of how many <a class="inlinePopup" href="#inlineCalorie">calories</a> you are eating.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Join a local slimming club if you think this may help you.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>With support, we can make simple changes that help us to feel better physically and mentally and to maintain good brain health.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>If you choose food from the Mediterranean Diet, eat more fruit and vegetables every day, and use olive oil instead of butter or margarine, your diet and your brain health will improve.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div style="display:none;">\r\n<div id="inlineCognitive" style="padding:10px; background:#fff;">\r\n<p>Cognitive function refers to memory, the ability to learn new information, process thoughts, speech and reading comprehension.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div id="inlineCalorie" style="padding:10px; background:#fff;">\r\n<p>A calorie is a unit of energy. It describes how much energy your body gets from eating or drinking. Most food and drinks contain calories. If you eat or drink more calories than you need, the leftover calories are converted to fat. If you only eat and drink the recommended daily number of calories, and if you also take enough exercise, you will stay within a healthy weight range. Being active is important because physical activity burns calories.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>', '<h1>Obesity</h1>\r\n\r\n<h2 class="h-color">Room for improvement</h2>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Your profile tells us that your BMI is &hellip;over 30&hellip;.. <a href="http://www.nhs.uk/Tools/Pages/Healthyweightcalculator.aspx">What is BMI and obesity?</a> There is room to improve your diet and your level of physical activity. Just a few small changes can lower your BMI, improve your brain health, and reduce your risk of dementia later in life.</li>\r\n	<li>BMI stands for body mass index. It is a formula used to check whether a person is underweight, overweight or at a healthy weight. The formula divides your weight by the square of your height to get a BMI score. Anyone with a BMI score of between 18.5 to 25 is considered a healthy weight, while 25 to 30 is overweight. A score of more than 30 is described as obese. <a href="http://www.nhs.uk/Tools/Pages/Healthyweightcalculator.aspx">Click here to calculate your BMI</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>What we know</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Obesity in middle age could increase the risk of dementia later in life.</li>\r\n	<li>Studies on <strong><a class="inlinePopup" href="#inlineCognitive">cognitive function</a></strong> and body mass index (<a href="http://www.nhs.uk/Tools/Pages/Healthyweightcalculator.aspx">BMI</a>) found that obese people have more trouble on memory and reasoning tests.</li>\r\n	<li>High blood pressure is often associated with obesity and could increase the risk of dementia later in life.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>A quick guide to obesity</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>A person who is obese has so much excess body fat that his or her health may suffer. Obesity is a medical condition.</li>\r\n	<li>Body mass index (<a href="http://www.nhs.uk/Tools/Pages/Healthyweightcalculator.aspx">BMI</a>) is a formula used to check whether a person is at a healthy weight for their height. A person is considered obese if they have a BMI of 30 or more.</li>\r\n	<li>Obesity has many causes and is not just about eating too much food.</li>\r\n	<li>Many of us are less physically active than our parents or grandparents were. Instead of walking everywhere, we travel in cars or on public transport. Many of us also have jobs that require us to sit for most of the day.</li>\r\n	<li>Lowering your BMI to a healthy level is not only good for your physical health but also improves your brain health.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="" src="images/riskfactors/diet/goal.jpg" /></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>What can I do?</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>To lose weight, you need to reduce the number of <a class="inlinePopup" href="#inlineCalorie">calories</a> you eat and drink every day and increase the amount of exercise you get.</li>\r\n	<li>If you are not physically active, you should ask your GP about the type of exercise you should do and how much, depending on how fit you are.</li>\r\n	<li>You can start by spending less time sitting at your computer or in front of the television.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>Take more exercise!</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Build up slowly. Choose physical activities that you enjoy. You&rsquo;ll be more likely to keep doing them then.</li>\r\n	<li>Start with activities that you can fit into your everyday life, like walking, gardening or taking the stairs instead of the lift</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="" src="images/riskfactors/obesity/walk.png" /></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Be realistic</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Set realistic weight loss goals.</li>\r\n	<li>Keep a food diary. This is a good way to keep track of how many <a class="inlinePopup" href="#inlineCalorie">calories</a> you are eating.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Join a local slimming club if you think this may help you.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>With support, we can make simple changes that help us to feel better physically and mentally and to maintain good brain health.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>How does my plan work?</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>The plan is meant to help you lose weight. A weight loss of 5%-10% will be good for your heart and your brain health.</li>\r\n	<li>Below are three goals that can help you lose weight by changing your diet and by exercising.</li>\r\n	<li>Remember, if you are not enjoying the changes to your diet or exercise habits, you will find it harder to keep going.&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;Choose one of the goals below. If you find it hard to fit these changes into your lifestyle, then come back and choose another goal!</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Choosing one of the goals above will help you lose weight and improve your BMI. It may take some time to get your BMI below 30. But remember that making simple changes to your diet and taking more exercise may help you to improve your overall brain health score. The plan is meant to help you make positive changes to your diet and exercise habits.</li>\r\n	<li>Choosing food from the Mediterranean Diet is a good way to improve your diet and, in turn, your brain health. Your brain will also benefit if you eat more fruit and vegetables every day and use olive oil instead of butter or margarine.</li>\r\n	<li>If you make simple changes to your diet, take more exercise, and choose one of the goals above, you will improve your overall brain health score.</li>\r\n	<li>If you choose food from the Mediterranean Diet, eat more fruit and vegetables every day, and use olive oil instead of butter or margarine, your diet and your brain health will improve.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div style="display:none;">\r\n<div id="inlineCognitive" style="padding:10px; background:#fff;">\r\n<p>Cognitive function refers to memory, the ability to learn new information, process thoughts, speech and reading comprehension.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div id="inlineCalorie" style="padding:10px; background:#fff;">\r\n<p>A calorie is a unit of energy. It describes how much energy your body gets from eating or drinking. Most food and drinks contain calories. If you eat or drink more calories than you need, the leftover calories are converted to fat. If you only eat and drink the recommended daily number of calories, and if you also take enough exercise, you will stay within a healthy weight range. Being active is important because physical activity burns calories.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n', '<h3>Other Supports</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>NHS advice on losing weight:</p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href="http://www.nhs.uk/livewell/loseweight/Pages/Loseweighthome.aspx">http://www.nhs.uk/livewell/loseweight/Pages/Loseweighthome.aspx</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>NHS 12 week weight loss plan (from above site) &ndash; pdf:</p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href="http://www.nhs.uk/Tools/Documents/WEIGHT-LOSS-PACK/all-weeks.pdf">http://www.nhs.uk/Tools/Documents/WEIGHT-LOSS-PACK/all-weeks.pdf</a></p>'),
	(8, 'en', 'Cognitive Activity', 'images/libra/cognitive_activity_amber.png', '<h1>Cognitive Activity</h1>\r\n\r\n<h2 class="h-color">Keep this up!</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Your profile tells us that you are cognitively active. Keep this up!<br />\r\nWhile many of us know how to keep physically active, we may not think about keeping our brains active, or have time for it.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Below you will find information about activities that can help you maintain your current level of cognitive activity in order to keep your brain healthy</p>\r\n\r\n<p>As we age, it is important to remain cognitively active to maintain our <a class="inlinePopup" href="#inlineCognitive">cognitive function</a>.<br />\r\nLearning new things and doing activities that challenge you is an excellent way to keep your brain healthy</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="" src="images/riskfactors/cognitive/brain.png" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Activities that stimulate you mentally, physically and socially will keep your brain healthy and help prevent dementia.<br />\r\nFor a healthy brain, you need to look after your brain, body and heart. Brain health is especially important once you reach middle age. That is when changes start to occur.<br />\r\nResearch suggests that people who have few friends nearby and who spend a lot of time alone have a higher risk of dementia.<br />\r\nAlso people with little formal&nbsp; education and people in mid-life who do not exercise their brains much run a higher risk of developing dementia later in life.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="" src="images/riskfactors/cognitive/games.png" /></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>What can you do?</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Train your brain with crossword puzzles or online brain-training exercises.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Join your local library. This is a great alternative to buying books, and the staff can recommend interesting books on all sorts of topics.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Consider volunteering. This is a great way to meet new people while doing something that will benefit your community.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Learn a new language. Many local libraries offer free language classes. You can also borrow language tapes from the library to take home.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Join or start a book club with friends and neighbours.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you like music, learn to play an instrument or join a local choir or music group. Post an ad at your local college or music school; music students may be willing to give you lessons for a relatively low fee.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you love to dance, check out local classes in your area. You will find everything from ballroom and salsa to hip-hop.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Go to concerts. Live music need not be expensive. There are many places that have free music events throughout the year.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Check out adult education classes. They offer everything from sewing to Greek philosophy!</li>\r\n	<li>Get out in the garden more. Many communities now have allotments where people can grow their own vegetables.</li>\r\n	<li>Join a local amateur dramatic society. This is great fun, but learning lines is also good for your memory!</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Activities that are good for brain health do not need to be expensive or boring.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Anything that stimulates you and that you enjoy is good for your brain!</p>\r\n\r\n<div style="display:none;">\r\n<div id="inlineCognitive" style="padding:10px; background:#fff;">\r\n<p>Cognitive function refers to memory, the ability to learn new information, process thoughts, speech and reading comprehension.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>', '<h1>Cognitive Activity</h1>\r\n\r\n<h2 class="h-color">Room for improvement</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Your profile tells us that there is room to improve your social life and exercise your brain more.<br />\r\nWhile many of us know how to keep physically active, we may not think about keeping our brains active, or have time for it.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Below you will find information about activities that can help you keep your brain healthy.<br />\r\nYou will also find your personalised plan.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>As we age, it is important to remain cognitively active to maintain our <a class="inlinePopup" href="#inlineCognitive">cognitive function</a>.<br />\r\nLearning new things and doing activities that challenge you is an excellent way to keep your brain healthy</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="" src="images/riskfactors/cognitive/brain.png" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Activities that stimulate you mentally, physically and socially will keep your brain healthy and help prevent dementia.<br />\r\nFor a healthy brain, you need to look after your brain, body and heart. Brain health is especially important once you reach middle age. That is when changes start to occur.<br />\r\nResearch suggests that people who have few friends nearby and who spend a lot of time alone have a higher risk of dementia.<br />\r\nAlso people with little formal&nbsp; education and people in mid-life who do not exercise their brains much run a higher risk of developing dementia later in life.<br />\r\nCognitive function refers to memory, the ability to learn new information, process thoughts, speech and reading comprehension.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="" src="images/riskfactors/cognitive/games.png" /></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>What can you do?</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Train your brain with crossword puzzles or online brain-training exercises.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Join your local library. This is a great alternative to buying books, and the staff can recommend interesting books on all sorts of topics.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Consider volunteering. This is a great way to meet new people while doing something that will benefit your community.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Learn a new language. Many local libraries offer free language classes. You can also borrow language tapes from the library to take home.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Join or start a book club with friends and neighbours.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you like music, learn to play an instrument or join a local choir or music group. Post an ad at your local college or music school; music students may be willing to give you lessons for a relatively low fee.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you love to dance, check out local classes in your area. You will find everything from ballroom and salsa to hip-hop.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Go to concerts. Live music need not be expensive. There are many places that have free music events throughout the year.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Check out adult education classes. They offer everything from sewing to Greek philosophy!</li>\r\n	<li>Get out in the garden more. Many communities now have allotments where people can grow their own vegetables.</li>\r\n	<li>Join a local amateur dramatic society. This is great fun, but learning lines is also good for your memory!</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Activities that are good for brain health do not need to be expensive or boring.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Anything that stimulates you and that you enjoy is good for your brain!</p>\r\n\r\n<div style="display:none;">\r\n<div id="inlineCognitive" style="padding:10px; background:#fff;">\r\n<p>Cognitive function refers to memory, the ability to learn new information, process thoughts, speech and reading comprehension.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>', '<h3>Further Supports</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><a href="http://www.citizensinformation.ie/en/"><strong>http://www.citizensinformation.ie/en/</strong></a></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Provides information on community services and access to those services</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><a href="http://www.volunteer.ie/"><strong>http://www.volunteer.ie/</strong></a></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>If you are thinking about volunteering this site will give you information on groups and organisations who take on volunteers.</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Adult Education Courses</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href="http://www.courses.ie/"><strong>http://www.courses.ie/</strong></a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href="http://www.aontas.com/"><strong>http://www.aontas.com/</strong></a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Outdoor Activities</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href="http://www.allotments.ie/"><strong>http://www.allotments.ie/</strong></a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href="http://www.dublincity.ie/YourCouncil/LocalAreaServices/SouthCentralArea/Pages/AllotmentsandCommunityGardens.aspx"><strong>http://www.dublincity.ie/YourCouncil/LocalAreaServices/SouthCentralArea/Pages/AllotmentsandCommunityGardens.aspx</strong></a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>These websites offer the user information on securing an allotment in your local community</p>'),
	(8, 'fr', 'Activit Cognitive', 'images/libra/cognitive_activity_amber.png', '<h1>Activit&eacute; Cognitive</h1>\r\n\r\n<h2>Continuez comme &ccedil;a&nbsp;!</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Votre profil nous informe que vous &ecirc;tre actif sur le plan cognitif. Continuez comme &ccedil;a&nbsp;!&nbsp;<br />\r\nBeaucoup d&#39;entre nous savent comment rester physiquement actif, mais nous ne pensons pas toujours, ou n&#39;avons pas le temps de maintenir notre cerveau actif.<br />\r\nCi-dessous vous trouverez des informations sur les activit&eacute;s permettant de maintenir votre cerveau en bonne sant&eacute;. Vous trouverez &eacute;galement votre plan personnalis&eacute;.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nQuand on vieillit, il est important de rester actif sur le plan cognitif pour garder notre fonctionnement cognitif. Apprendre de nouvelles choses et pratiquer des activit&eacute;s qui vous stimulent sont d&#39;excellentes mani&egrave;res pour maintenir votre cerveau en bonne sant&eacute;.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="" src="images/riskfactors/cognitive/brain.png" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Les activit&eacute;s qui vous stimulent mentalement, physiquement et socialement permettent de garder le cerveau en bonne sant&eacute; et de pr&eacute;venir la d&eacute;mence.<br />\r\nPour avoir un cerveau en bonne sant&eacute;, vous devez en prendre soin, corps et &acirc;me. C&#39;est d&#39;autant plus important quand on arrive &agrave; la cinquantaine: les changement commencent &agrave; se produire &agrave; cette p&eacute;riode.<br />\r\nLes recherches sugg&egrave;rent que les personnes qui n&#39;ont que quelques amis pr&egrave;s d&#39;eux et qui passent beaucoup de temps seules sont plus susceptibles de devenir d&eacute;ments.<br />\r\nDe m&ecirc;me, les personnes qui ont eu une faible &eacute;ducation scolaire et les personnes d&#39;&acirc;ge m&ucirc;r qui n&#39;exercent pas beaucoup leur cerveau courent plus de risques de d&eacute;velopper une d&eacute;mence plus tard dans leur vie.<br />\r\nLe fonctionnement cognitif renvoie &agrave; la m&eacute;moire, la capacit&eacute; &agrave; apprendre de nouvelles informations, les m&eacute;canismes de la pens&eacute;e, la compr&eacute;hension &eacute;crite et orale.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="" src="images/riskfactors/cognitive/games.png" /></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Que pouvez-vous faire?</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>- Entrainez votre cerveau avec des mots crois&eacute;s ou des exercices d&#39;entrainement pour le cerveau sur internet.<br />\r\n- Inscrivez vous dans votre biblioth&egrave;que locale. C&#39;est une bonne alternative &agrave; l&#39;achat de livres et l&#39;&eacute;quipe de la biblioth&egrave;que peut vous recommander de bons ouvrages sur tous les sujets.<br />\r\n- Envisagez le volontariat. C&#39;est un bon moyen pour rencontrer de nouvelles personnes en faisant quelque chose qui b&eacute;n&eacute;ficie &agrave; la communaut&eacute;.<br />\r\n- Apprenez une nouvelle langue. De nombreuses biblioth&egrave;ques locales proposent des cours de langues gratuits. Vous pouvez &eacute;galement emprunter documents sonores &agrave; la biblioth&egrave;que et les &eacute;couter chez vous.<br />\r\n- Rejoigniez ou cr&eacute;ez un cercle de lecture avec des amis ou vos voisins.<br />\r\n- Si vous aimez la musique, apprenez &agrave; jouer d&#39;un instrument ou inscrivez vous &agrave; une chorale ou &agrave; un groupe de musique. Mettez une annonce &agrave; une universit&eacute; proche de chez vous ou dans une &eacute;cole de musique: des &eacute;tudiants en musique cherchent parfois &agrave; donner des cours &agrave; un prix assez bas.<br />\r\n- Si vous aimez danser, v&eacute;rifiez ce qui se fait pr&egrave;s de chez vous, vous trouverez tout type de danses, des danses de salons et salsa jusqu&#39;au hip-hop.<br />\r\n- Allez &agrave; des concerts. Ce n&#39;est pas n&eacute;cessairement cher. De nombreux endroits proposent des concerts gratuits tout au long de l&#39;ann&eacute;e.<br />\r\n- Jetez un &oelig;il aux cours pour adultes. Vous trouverez de tout, de la couture &agrave; la philosophie grecque.<br />\r\n- Sortez plus souvent dans le jardin. De nombreux quartiers ont d&eacute;sormais des lots de terre o&ugrave; l&#39;on peut faire pousser ses propres l&eacute;gumes.<br />\r\n- Inscrivez vous dans une troupe de th&eacute;&acirc;tre amateur pr&egrave;s de chez vous. C&#39;est tr&egrave;s amusant, mais en plus de cela, apprendre son texte est bon pour la m&eacute;moire!<br />\r\n<br />\r\nLes activit&eacute;s b&eacute;n&eacute;fiques &agrave; votre cerveau ne doivent pas forc&eacute;ment &ecirc;tre ch&egrave;res ou ennuyeuses.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nTout ce qui vous stimule et qui vous fait plaisir est bon pour votre cerveau!</p>', '<h1>Activit&eacute; Cognitive</h1>\r\n\r\n<h2>Une am&eacute;lioration est possible</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Votre profil nous annonce que vous pouvez toujours am&eacute;liorer votre vie sociale et entrainer votre cerveau.<br />\r\nBeaucoup d&#39;entre nous savent comment rester physiquement actif, mais nous ne pensons pas toujours, ou n&#39;avons pas le temps de maintenir notre cerveau actif.<br />\r\nCi-dessous vous trouverez des informations sur les activit&eacute;s permettant de maintenir votre cerveau en bonne sant&eacute;. Vous trouverez &eacute;galement votre plan personnalis&eacute;.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nQuand on vieillit, il est important de rester actif sur le plan cognitif pour garder notre fonctionnement cognitif. Apprendre de nouvelles choses et pratiquer des activit&eacute;s qui vous stimulent sont d&#39;excellentes mani&egrave;res pour maintenir votre cerveau en bonne sant&eacute;.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="" src="images/riskfactors/cognitive/brain.png" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\nLes activit&eacute;s qui vous stimulent mentalement, physiquement et socialement permettent de garder le cerveau en bonne sant&eacute; et de pr&eacute;venir la d&eacute;mence.<br />\r\nPour avoir un cerveau en bonne sant&eacute;, vous devez en prendre soin, corps et &acirc;me. C&#39;est d&#39;autant plus important quand on arrive &agrave; la cinquantaine: les changement commencent &agrave; se produire &agrave; cette p&eacute;riode.<br />\r\nLes recherches sugg&egrave;rent que les personnes qui n&#39;ont que quelques amis pr&egrave;s d&#39;eux et qui passent beaucoup de temps seules sont plus susceptibles de devenir d&eacute;ments.<br />\r\nDe m&ecirc;me, les personnes qui ont eu une faible &eacute;ducation scolaire et les personnes d&#39;&acirc;ge m&ucirc;r qui n&#39;exercent pas beaucoup leur cerveau courent plus de risques de d&eacute;velopper une d&eacute;mence plus tard dans leur vie.<br />\r\nLe fonctionnement cognitif renvoie &agrave; la m&eacute;moire, la capacit&eacute; &agrave; apprendre de nouvelles informations, les m&eacute;canismes de la pens&eacute;e, la compr&eacute;hension &eacute;crite et orale.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="" src="images/riskfactors/cognitive/games.png" /></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Que pouvez-vous faire?<br />\r\n&nbsp;</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>- Entrainez votre cerveau avec des mots crois&eacute;s ou des exercices d&#39;entrainement pour le cerveau sur internet.<br />\r\n- Inscrivez vous dans votre biblioth&egrave;que locale. C&#39;est une bonne alternative &agrave; l&#39;achat de livres et l&#39;&eacute;quipe de la biblioth&egrave;que peut vous recommander de bons ouvrages sur tous les sujets.<br />\r\n- Envisagez le volontariat. C&#39;est un bon moyen pour rencontrer de nouvelles personnes en faisant quelque chose qui b&eacute;n&eacute;ficie &agrave; la communaut&eacute;.<br />\r\n- Apprenez une nouvelle langue. De nombreuses biblioth&egrave;ques locales proposent des cours de langues gratuits. Vous pouvez &eacute;galement emprunter documents sonores &agrave; la biblioth&egrave;que et les &eacute;couter chez vous.<br />\r\n- Rejoigniez ou cr&eacute;ez un cercle de lecture avec des amis ou vos voisins.<br />\r\n- Si vous aimez la musique, apprenez &agrave; jouer d&#39;un instrument ou inscrivez vous &agrave; une chorale ou &agrave; un groupe de musique. Mettez une annonce &agrave; une universit&eacute; proche de chez vous ou dans une &eacute;cole de musique: des &eacute;tudiants en musique cherchent parfois &agrave; donner des cours &agrave; un prix assez bas.<br />\r\n- Si vous aimez danser, v&eacute;rifiez ce qui se fait pr&egrave;s de chez vous, vous trouverez tout type de danses, des danses de salons et salsa jusqu&#39;au hip-hop.<br />\r\n- Allez &agrave; des concerts. Ce n&#39;est pas n&eacute;cessairement cher. De nombreux endroits proposent des concerts gratuits tout au long de l&#39;ann&eacute;e.<br />\r\n- Jetez un &oelig;il aux cours pour adultes. Vous trouverez de tout, de la couture &agrave; la philosophie grecque.<br />\r\n- Sortez plus souvent dans le jardin. De nombreux quartiers ont d&eacute;sormais des lots de terre o&ugrave; l&#39;on peut faire pousser ses propres l&eacute;gumes.<br />\r\n- Inscrivez vous dans une troupe de th&eacute;&acirc;tre amateur pr&egrave;s de chez vous. C&#39;est tr&egrave;s amusant, mais en plus de cela, apprendre son texte est bon pour la m&eacute;moire!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Les activit&eacute;s b&eacute;n&eacute;fiques &agrave; votre cerveau ne doivent pas forc&eacute;ment &ecirc;tre ch&egrave;res ou ennuyeuses.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nTout ce qui vous stimule et qui vous fait plaisir est bon pour votre cerveau!</p>', ' '),
