et de l&eacute;gumes, de l&eacute;gumes secs, d&rsquo;aliments complets et de fruits secs.</li>\r\n	<li>Consommez moins de sucre.</li>\r\n	<li>Les fruits et les l&eacute;gumes jouent un r&ocirc;le important au sein d&rsquo;une alimentation &eacute;quilibr&eacute;e En consommant suffisamment de fruits et de l&eacute;gumes au quotidien, vous pourrez &eacute;viter des maladies graves de type cardiovasculaires ainsi que certains cancers.<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	<img alt="" src="images/riskfactors/diet/vegies.png" /></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>Les alternatives sant&eacute;</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Mangez plus de poisson chaque semaine. Consommez-en deux fois par semaine (saumon, maquereau ou sardines) avec de l&rsquo;huile.<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\nPrenez de l&rsquo;huile d&rsquo;olive &agrave; la place du beurre. Plut&ocirc;t que de faire frire votre nourriture, faites-la griller, pr&eacute;parez-la au four ou &agrave; la vapeur.<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\nOptez pour les p&acirc;tes et le riz complets.<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\nAjoutez des l&eacute;gumes secs (ou l&eacute;gumineuses) &agrave; votre alimentation quotidienne : pensez aux haricots rouges ou verts ainsi qu&rsquo;aux lentilles.<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\nEn guise d&rsquo;en-cas, prenez des fruits, des fruits &agrave; coque ou bien des l&eacute;gumes.<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong>Essayez autant que possible de ne pas sauter les repas, car dans ce cas vous &ecirc;tes susceptible de manger de plus grandes portions pour vous rattraper. Il vous faudra diminuer autant que faire se peut votre consommation de caf&eacute;, de th&eacute; et de boissons sucr&eacute;es pour privil&eacute;gier l&rsquo;eau.</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\nSi votre Indice de Masse Corporelle d&eacute;passe la limite recommand&eacute;e (c&rsquo;est-&agrave;-dire au-dessus de 25), vous devrez diminuer votre apport en calories ; cela est possible si vous suivez les conseils dispens&eacute;s ci-dessus. N&rsquo;oubliez pas de limiter &eacute;galement la taille de vos portions alimentaires, afin de ne pas d&eacute;passer l&rsquo;apport en calories recommand&eacute;.<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\nL&rsquo;IMC est une formule que l&rsquo;on utilise pour v&eacute;rifier si une personne est trop maigre, en surpoids ou si son poids est dans les normes. Cette formule divise votre poids par le carr&eacute; de votre taille afin d&rsquo;obtenir une estimation de votre indice. Une personne poss&eacute;dant un indice entre 18,5 et 25 est consid&eacute;r&eacute;e comme en bonne sant&eacute; ; de 25 &agrave; 30, la personne est en surpoids. Une estimation sup&eacute;rieure &agrave; 30 correspond &agrave; une personne ob&egrave;se. Cliquez ici pour calculer votre IMC.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>', ' '),
	(9, 'sc', 'Diet', 'images/libra/diet_amber.png', '<h1>Diet</h1>\r\n\r\n<h2 class="h-color">Keep this up!</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Your profile tells us that your current diet is healthy. Keep this up!<br />\r\nBelow you will find information on the importance of a healthy diet to your brain health. You may find new ways of incorporating healthy foods into your everyday diet!</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>A healthy diet is good for our overall health but it is also good for our brain health</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Researchers have found that diet and physical activity have a positive effect on our brain health.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Our eating habits may also play an important role in protecting us against dementia.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="" src="images/riskfactors/diet/pyramid.png" /></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>The Mediterranean Diet is thought to protect against dementia.</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The Mediterranean Diet has lots of fish, vegetables, pulses (beans, also known as legumes), fruit, cereals and olive oil, and only small amounts of dairy, meat and butter or margarine.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>To eat a healthy and balanced diet, you need to combine several different types of foods - from each of the main food groups - in the right amounts. That way your body gets all the nutrients it needs while you maintain a healthy weight.&nbsp; This means you should eat:</li>\r\n	<li>Whole-grain breads, pasta and rice if available</li>\r\n	<li>Plenty of fruit and vegetables</li>\r\n	<li>Some milk, cheese and yoghurt</li>\r\n	<li>Some meat, fish, eggs, beans and other non-dairy sources of protein, and</li>\r\n	<li>Just a small amount of foods and drinks high in fat and/or sugar</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Eat more vegetables and fruit. </strong>Eat fruit and vegetables at every meal and for snacks as well. Carrots, celery, bananas and apples are easy to have on hand and make satisfying snacks. Fruit salads are a great way to eat a wide variety of healthy fruit.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Switch to whole-grain bread. </strong>Whole grains contain very few unhealthy fats. Try using whole-grain rice and pasta. Replace sugary breakfast cereals with porridge and add in blueberries or other fruit. If you need more sweetness, use honey instead of sugar.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Eat nuts. </strong>Try almonds, cashews, pistachios and walnuts. Try natural peanut butter. Nuts can be added to any meal but are also a great snack when you&rsquo;re out and about. Don&rsquo;t overdo it because nuts can be high in <a class="inlinePopup" href="#inlineCalorie">calories</a>. We recommend a handful of unsalted nuts 3 times per week. .</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Use olive oil </strong>as a healthy replacement for butter or margarine. Drizzle it on vegetables and bread. Make your own salad dressing by using a little olive oil, red wine or balsamic vinegar and crushed garlic. Add a squeeze of lemon juice if you wish. Olive oil, garlic, leeks and onions are a healthy alternative to shop-bought pasta sauces.<br />\r\n	<img alt="" src="images/riskfactors/diet/oil.png" /></li>\r\n	<li><strong>Eat fish </strong>at least twice a week. Salmon, trout and tuna are healthy choices. Grilling, baking or steaming fish is not only healthy but also takes very little time and effort. If you&rsquo;re on a budget, choose tinned sardines, tuna or mackerel. Eat it on whole-grain bread for a healthy lunch or evening snack.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Go low fat</strong>. Cut down on high-fat dairy products. Switch to skimmed milk, fat-free yogurt and low-fat cheese. Try frozen yogurt or natural yogurt as a healthy alternative to ice cream. Add in any fruit you wish for that extra sweetness!</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h2 class="h-color">What can I do?</h2>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Watch the number of <a class="inlinePopup" href="#inlineCalorie">calories</a> you consume and maintain a healthy weight.</li>\r\n	<li>Limit the amount of fat in your diet. Use less animal fat like butter and margarine (known as saturated fats) and more vegetable fat like olive oil (known as unsaturated fats). Try to eliminate fast food, fried food and greasy snacks, which contain unhealthy trans-fatty acids.</li>\r\n	<li>Eat more fruits and vegetables, beans, whole grains and nuts.</li>\r\n	<li>Eat less sugar.</li>\r\n	<li>Fruit and vegetables are important parts of a healthy diet. Eating enough fruit and vegetables every day helps you avoid serious diseases, such as cardiovascular diseases and certain cancers.<br />\r\n	<img alt="" src="images/riskfactors/diet/vegies.png" /></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>Healthy Options</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Eat more fish every week. Have oily fish such as salmon, mackerel or sardines twice a week.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Switch to olive oil. Instead of frying your food, choose grilling, baking or steaming.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Use whole-grain pasta or rice.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Add pulses (or legumes) to your everyday diet, for example peas, kidney beans or lentils.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Snack on fruit, nuts or vegetables.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Try not to skip meals, as you are more likely to eat larger portions when you do eat.<br />\r\nCut out/down on coffee/tea and sugary drinks and drink more water.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If your BMI is above the recommended limits for a healthy weight (over 25), you should reduce your <a class="inlinePopup" href="#inlineCalorie">calorie</a> intake. You can do this by following the advice above. Remember to limit your portion size as well, and not to exceed the recommended number of <a class="inlinePopup" href="#inlineCalorie">calories</a>.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>BMI is a formula used to check whether a person is underweight, overweight or at a healthy weight. The formula divides your weight by the square of your height to get a BMI score. Anyone with a BMI score of between 18.5 to 25 is considered healthy, while 25 to 30 is overweight. A score of more than 30 is described as obese. <a href="http://www.nhs.uk/Tools/Pages/Healthyweightcalculator.aspx">Click here to calculate your BMI</a>.</p>\r\n\r\n<div style="display:none;">\r\n<div id="inlineCalorie" style="padding:10px; background:#fff;">\r\n<p>A calorie is a unit of energy. It describes how much energy your body gets from eating or drinking. Most food and drinks contain calories. If you eat or drink more calories than you need, the leftover calories are converted to fat. If you only eat and drink the recommended number of daily calories, you will stay within a healthy weight range. Being active is also important because physical activity burns calories.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>', '<h1>Diet</h1>\r\n\r\n<h2 class="h-color">Room for improvement</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Your profile tells us that your current diet could be improved.<br />\r\nMaking some small changes to your diet will help you maintain your brain health.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Below you will find information to help you make healthy eating part of your everyday routine.<br />\r\nYou will also find your personalised plan. This gives you a number of goals to choose from to help you develop healthy eating habits!</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>A healthy diet is good for our overall health but it is also good for our brain health</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Researchers have found that diet and physical activity have a positive effect on our brain health.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Our eating habits may also play an important role in protecting us against dementia.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="" src="images/riskfactors/diet/pyramid.png" /></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>The Mediterranean Diet is thought to protect against dementia.</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The Mediterranean Diet has lots of fish, vegetables, pulses (beans, also known as legumes), fruit, cereals and olive oil, and only small amounts of dairy, meat and butter or margarine.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>To eat a healthy and balanced diet, you need to combine several different types of foods - from each of the main food groups - in the right amounts. That way your body gets all the nutrients it needs while you maintain a healthy weight.&nbsp; This means you should eat:</li>\r\n	<li>Whole-grain breads, pasta and rice if available</li>\r\n	<li>Plenty of fruit and vegetables</li>\r\n	<li>Some milk, cheese and yoghurt</li>\r\n	<li>Some meat, fish, eggs, beans and other non-dairy sources of protein, and</li>\r\n	<li>Just a small amount of foods and drinks high in fat and/or sugar</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Eat more vegetables and fruit. </strong>Eat fruit and vegetables at every meal and for snacks as well. Carrots, celery, bananas and apples are easy to have on hand and make satisfying snacks. Fruit salads are a great way to eat a wide variety of healthy fruit.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Switch to whole-grain bread. </strong>Whole grains contain very few unhealthy fats. Try using whole-grain rice and pasta. Replace sugary breakfast cereals with porridge and add in blueberries or other fruit. If you need more sweetness, use honey instead of sugar.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Eat nuts. </strong>Try almonds, cashews, pistachios and walnuts. Try natural peanut butter. Nuts can be added to any meal but are also a great snack when you&rsquo;re out and about. Don&rsquo;t overdo it because nuts can be high in <a class="inlinePopup" href="#inlineCalorie">calories</a>. We recommend a handful of unsalted nuts 3 times per week. .</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Use olive oil </strong>as a healthy replacement for butter or margarine. Drizzle it on vegetables and bread. Make your own salad dressing by using a little olive oil, red wine or balsamic vinegar and crushed garlic. Add a squeeze of lemon juice if you wish. Olive oil, garlic, leeks and onions are a healthy alternative to shop-bought pasta sauces.<br />\r\n	<img alt="" src="images/riskfactors/diet/oil.png" /></li>\r\n	<li><strong>Eat fish </strong>at least twice a week. Salmon, trout and tuna are healthy choices. Grilling, baking or steaming fish is not only healthy but also takes very little time and effort. If you&rsquo;re on a budget, choose tinned sardines, tuna or mackerel. Eat it on whole-grain bread for a healthy lunch or evening snack.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Go low fat</strong>. Cut down on high-fat dairy products. Switch to skimmed milk, fat-free yogurt and low-fat cheese. Try frozen yogurt or natural yogurt as a healthy alternative to ice cream. Add in any fruit you wish for that extra sweetness!</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h2 class="h-color">What can I do?</h2>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Watch the number of <a class="inlinePopup" href="#inlineCalorie">calories</a> you consume and maintain a healthy weight.</li>\r\n	<li>Limit the amount of fat in your diet. Use less animal fat like butter and margarine (known as saturated fats) and more vegetable fat like olive oil (known as unsaturated fats). Try to eliminate fast food, fried food and greasy snacks, which contain unhealthy trans-fatty acids.</li>\r\n	<li>Eat more fruits and vegetables, beans, whole grains and nuts.</li>\r\n	<li>Eat less sugar.</li>\r\n	<li>Fruit and vegetables are important parts of a healthy diet. Eating enough fruit and vegetables every day helps you avoid serious diseases, such as cardiovascular diseases and certain cancers.<br />\r\n	<img alt="" src="images/riskfactors/diet/vegies.png" /></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>Healthy Options</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Eat more fish every week. Have oily fish such as salmon, mackerel or sardines twice a week.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Switch to olive oil. Instead of frying your food, choose grilling, baking or steaming.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Use whole-grain pasta or rice.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Add pulses (or legumes) to your everyday diet, for example peas, kidney beans or lentils.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Snack on fruit, nuts or vegetables.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Try not to skip meals, as you are more likely to eat larger portions when you do eat.<br />\r\nCut out/down on coffee/tea and sugary drinks and drink more water.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If your BMI is above the recommended limits for a healthy weight (over 25), you should reduce your <a class="inlinePopup" href="#inlineCalorie">calorie</a> intake. You can do this by following the advice above. Remember to limit your portion size as well, and not to exceed the recommended number of <a class="inlinePopup" href="#inlineCalorie">calories</a>.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>BMI is a formula used to check whether a person is underweight, overweight or at a healthy weight. The formula divides your weight by the square of your height to get a BMI score. Anyone with a BMI score of between 18.5 to 25 is considered healthy, while 25 to 30 is overweight. A score of more than 30 is described as obese. <a href="http://www.nhs.uk/Tools/Pages/Healthyweightcalculator.aspx">Click here to calculate your BMI</a>.</p>\r\n\r\n<div style="display:none;">\r\n<div id="inlineCalorie" style="padding:10px; background:#fff;">\r\n<p>A calorie is a unit of energy. It describes how much energy your body gets from eating or drinking. Most food and drinks contain calories. If you eat or drink more calories than you need, the leftover calories are converted to fat. If you only eat and drink the recommended number of daily calories, you will stay within a healthy weight range. Being active is also important because physical activity burns calories.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>', '<h3>Further Supports</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>NHS &ndash; the eatwell plate:</p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href="http://www.nhs.uk/Livewell/Goodfood/Pages/eatwell-plate.aspx">http://www.nhs.uk/Livewell/Goodfood/Pages/eatwell-plate.aspx</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Patient.co.uk &ndash; healthy eating advice:</p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href="http://www.patient.co.uk/health/healthy-eating">http://www.patient.co.uk/health/healthy-eating</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>British Nutrition Foundation &ndash; provides advice on nutrition:</p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href="http://www.nutrition.org.uk/">http://www.nutrition.org.uk/</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>myfitnesspal &ndash; US based site with food tracker (available online and as a free app), a lot of UK food nutritional info:</p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href="http://www.myfitnesspal.com/">http://www.myfitnesspal.com/</a></p>'),
	(10, 'en', 'Cholesterol', 'images/libra/cholesteral_amber.png', '<h1>Cholesterol</h1>\r\n\r\n<h2 class="h-color">Keep this up!</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Your profile tells us that you do not have high cholesterol.<br />\r\nKeep this up!<br />\r\nEvidence tells us that a healthy cholesterol level can improve your long term brain health<br />\r\nBelow you will find information on maintaining your cholesterol at a healthy level</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>What causes high cholesterol?</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Eating a diet that is high in saturated fats</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Lack of physical exercise</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Smoking</p>\r\n\r\n<p>High alcohol intake</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Liver or kidney disease</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Know your fats!</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Unsaturated fats</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Small amounts of unsaturated fat in your diet can be healthy. This type of fat can help reduce cholesterol levels.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The traditional Mediterranean <a href="infos-riskfactor.html?riskfactor=9">Diet</a> includes plenty of olive oil and only small amounts of animal fat. It is good for your heart and blood circulation (your cardiovascular health).</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="" src="images/riskfactors/cholesterol/img1.png" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Foods high in unsaturated fats include</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>oily fish</p>\r\n\r\n<p>avocados</p>\r\n\r\n<p>nuts and seeds</p>\r\n\r\n<p>sunflower, rapeseed and olive oil</p>\r\n\r\n<p>vegetable oils</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Foods to avoid!</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Avoid foods containing saturated fats or eat them only on rare occasions.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>These foods include:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>fatty cuts of meat and meat products, such as sausages and pies</p>\r\n\r\n<p>butter and lard</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Foods to limit!</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="" style="margin:0;" src="images/riskfactors/cholesterol/img2.png" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>cream, soured cream, cr&egrave;me fraiche and ice cream</p>\r\n\r\n<p>cheese, particularly hard cheese</p>\r\n\r\n<p>cakes and biscuits</p>\r\n\r\n<p>chocolate</p>\r\n\r\n<p>coconut oil, coconut cream and palm oil</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The average man should have no more than 30 grams of saturated fat a day.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The average woman should have no more than 20 grams of saturated fat a day.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>To get an idea how much saturated fat you are consuming, take a look at the food labels of the foods you are eating.</p>\r\n', '<h1>Cholesterol</h1>\r\n\r\n<h2 class="h-color">Room for improvement</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Your profile tells us that you have high cholesterol. Evidence tells us that a healthy cholesterol level can improve your long term brain health</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>What causes high cholesterol?</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Eating a diet that is high in saturated fats</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Lack of physical exercise</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Smoking</p>\r\n\r\n<p>High alcohol intake</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Liver or kidney disease</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Know your fats!</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Unsaturated fats</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Small amounts of unsaturated fat in your diet can be healthy. This type of fat can help reduce cholesterol levels.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The traditional Mediterranean <a href="infos-riskfactor.html?riskfactor=9">Diet</a> includes plenty of olive oil and only small amounts of animal fat. It is good for your heart and blood circulation (your cardiovascular health).</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="" src="images/riskfactors/cholesterol/img1.png" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Foods high in unsaturated fats include</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>oily fish</p>\r\n\r\n<p>avocados</p>\r\n\r\n<p>nuts and seeds</p>\r\n\r\n<p>sunflower, rapeseed and olive oil</p>\r\n\r\n<p>vegetable oils</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Foods to avoid!</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Avoid foods containing saturated fats or eat them only on rare occasions.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>These foods include:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>fatty cuts of meat and meat products, such as sausages and pies</p>\r\n\r\n<p>butter and lard</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Foods to limit!</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="" style="margin:0;" src="images/riskfactors/cholesterol/img2.png" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>cream, soured cream, cr&egrave;me fraiche and ice cream</p>\r\n\r\n<p>cheese, particularly hard cheese</p>\r\n\r\n<p>cakes and biscuits</p>\r\n\r\n<p>chocolate</p>\r\n\r\n<p>coconut oil, coconut cream and palm oil</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The average man should have no more than 30 grams of saturated fat a day.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The average woman should have no more than 20 grams of saturated fat a day.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>To get an idea how much saturated fat you are consuming, take a look at the food labels of the foods you are eating.</p>\r\n', '<h3>Further Supports:</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Provides information, advice and support on diet and exercise to help you get your cholesterol down to a healthy level</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a href="http://www.irishheart.ie">www.irishheart.ie</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n'),
	(10, 'fr', 'Cholestrol', 'images/libra/cholesteral_amber.png', '<h1>Cholest&eacute;rol</h1>\r\n\r\n<h2>Continuez comme &ccedil;a&nbsp;!</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Votre profil nous annonce que vous n&rsquo;avez pas un taux de cholest&eacute;rol &eacute;lev&eacute;.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Continuez comme &ccedil;a&nbsp;!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Il est prouv&eacute; qu&rsquo;un taux de cholest&eacute;rol sain peut am&eacute;liorer &agrave; long terme la sant&eacute; du cerveau.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Ci-dessous vous trouverez les informations qui vous aideront &agrave; maintenir votre cholest&eacute;rol &agrave; un taux sain.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>&nbsp;</h3>\r\n\r\n<h3>Quelles sont les causes du cholest&eacute;rol&nbsp;?</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>- Avoir une alimentation trop riche en acides gras satur&eacute;s</p>\r\n\r\n<p>- Manque d&rsquo;exercice physique</p>\r\n\r\n<p>- Grande consommation d&rsquo;alcool</p>\r\n\r\n<p>- Probl&egrave;mes au foie ou aux reins</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Reconnaissez les graisses dans vos aliments!</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Graisses insatur&eacute;es </strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Les graisses insatur&eacute;es en petite quantit&eacute; dans votre alimentation peuvent &ecirc;tre b&eacute;n&eacute;fiques pour votre sant&eacute;. Ce type de graisses aide &agrave; r&eacute;duire le taux de cholest&eacute;rol.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Le <a href="infos-riskfactor.html?riskfactor=9">r&eacute;gime</a> traditionnel m&eacute;diterran&eacute;en comprend beaucoup d&rsquo;huile d&rsquo;olives et peu de graisses animales. C&rsquo;est bon pour le c&oelig;ur et la circulation sanguine.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="" src="images/riskfactors/cholesterol/img1.png" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Les aliments riches en graisses insatur&eacute;es comprennent&nbsp;:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>- le poisson gras</p>\r\n\r\n<p>- les avocats</p>\r\n\r\n<p>- les noix et graines</p>\r\n\r\n<p>- les huiles de tournesol, de colza et d&rsquo;olives</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Les aliments &agrave; &eacute;viter&nbsp;au maximum !</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>&Eacute;viter les aliments contenants des graisses satur&eacute;es ou en manger rarement, ces derniers comprennent&nbsp;:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>- la partie grasse de la viande et les plats &agrave; base de viande comme les saucisses ou les tartes.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>- le beurre et le lard</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Les aliments dont il faut limiter la consommation&nbsp;:</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="" style="margin:0;" src="images/riskfactors/cholesterol/img2.png" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>- cr&egrave;me, cr&egrave;me aigre, cr&egrave;me fraiche et glaces</p>\r\n\r\n<p>- fromage, en particulier les fromages &agrave; p&acirc;te dure</p>\r\n\r\n<p>- g&acirc;teaux et biscuits</p>\r\n\r\n<p>- chocolat</p>\r\n\r\n<p>- huile de coco, lait de coco et huile de palme</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>En moyenne, un homme ne devrait pas manger plus de 30g de graisses satur&eacute;es par jours.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>De m&ecirc;me, une femme ne devrait pas manger plus de 20g de graisses satur&eacute;es par jour.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Pour avoir une id&eacute;e de la quantit&eacute; de graisses satur&eacute;es que vous consommez, regardez attentivement les emballages de ce que vous mangez.</p>', '<h1>Cholest&eacute;rol</h1>\r\n\r\n<h2 class="h-color">Marge de progression</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Votre profil nous annonce que vous avez un taux de cholest&eacute;rol &eacute;lev&eacute;. Il est prouv&eacute; qu&rsquo;un bon taux de cholest&eacute;rol peut am&eacute;liorer la sant&eacute; du cerveau &agrave; long terme.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Ci-dessous vous trouverez les informations qui vous aideront &agrave; maintenir votre cholest&eacute;rol &agrave; un taux sain.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Quelles sont les causes du cholest&eacute;rol&nbsp;?</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>- Avoir une alimentation trop riche en acides gras satur&eacute;s</p>\r\n\r\n<p>- Manque d&rsquo;exercice physique</p>\r\n\r\n<p>- Grande consommation d&rsquo;alcool</p>\r\n\r\n<p>- Probl&egrave;mes au foie ou aux reins</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Reconnaissez les graisses dans vos aliments.</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Graisses insatur&eacute;es </strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Les graisses insatur&eacute;es en petite quantit&eacute; dans votre alimentation peuvent &ecirc;tre b&eacute;n&eacute;fiques pour votre sant&eacute;. Ce type de graisses aide &agrave; r&eacute;duire le taux de cholest&eacute;rol.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Le <a href="infos-riskfactor.html?riskfactor=9">r&eacute;gime</a> traditionnel m&eacute;diterran&eacute;en comprend beaucoup d&rsquo;huile d&rsquo;olives et peu de graisses animales. C&rsquo;est bon pour le c&oelig;ur et la circulation sanguine.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="" src="images/riskfactors/cholesterol/img1.png" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Les aliments riches en graisses insatur&eacute;es comprennent&nbsp;:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>- le poisson gras</p>\r\n\r\n<p>- les avocats</p>\r\n\r\n<p>- les noix et graines</p>\r\n\r\n<p>- les huiles de tournesol, de colza et d&rsquo;olives</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Les aliments &agrave; &eacute;viter&nbsp;au maximum !</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>&Eacute;viter les aliments contenants des graisses satur&eacute;es ou en manger rarement, ces derniers comprennent&nbsp;:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>- la partie grasse de la viande et les plats &agrave; base de viande comme les saucisses ou les tartes.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>- le beurre et le lard</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Les aliments dont il faut limiter la consommation :</h3>\r\n\r\n<h3>&nbsp;</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="" style="margin:0;" src="images/riskfactors/cholesterol/img2.png" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>- cr&egrave;me, cr&egrave;me aigre, cr&egrave;me fraiche et glaces</p>\r\n\r\n<p>- fromage, en particulier les fromages &agrave; p&acirc;te dure</p>\r\n\r\n<p>- g&acirc;teaux et biscuits</p>\r\n\r\n<p>- chocolat</p>\r\n\r\n<p>- huile de coco, lait de coco et huile de palme</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>En moyenne, un homme ne devrait pas manger plus de 30g de graisses satur&eacute;es par jours.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>De m&ecirc;me, une femme ne devrait pas manger plus de 20g de graisses satur&eacute;es par jour.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Pour avoir une id&eacute;e de la quantit&eacute; de graisses satur&eacute;es que vous consommez, regardez attentivement les emballages de ce que vous mangez.</p>', ''),
	(10, 'sc', 'Cholesterol', 'images/libra/cholesteral_amber.png', '<h1>Cholesterol</h1>\r\n\r\n<h2 class="h-color">Keep this up!</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Your profile tells us that you do not have high cholesterol.<br />\r\nKeep this up!<br />\r\nEvidence tells us that a healthy cholesterol level can improve your long term brain health<br />\r\nBelow you will find information on maintaining your cholesterol at a healthy level</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>What causes high cholesterol?</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Eating a diet that is high in saturated fats</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Lack of physical exercise</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Smoking</p>\r\n\r\n<p>High alcohol intake</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Liver or kidney disease</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Know your fats!</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Unsaturated fats</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Small amounts of unsaturated fat in your diet can be healthy. This type of fat can help reduce cholesterol levels.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The traditional Mediterranean <a href="infos-riskfactor.html?riskfactor=9">Diet</a> includes plenty of olive oil and only small amounts of animal fat. It is good for your heart and blood circulation (your cardiovascular health).</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="" src="images/riskfactors/cholesterol/img1.png" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Foods high in unsaturated fats include</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>oily fish</p>\r\n\r\n<p>avocados</p>\r\n\r\n<p>nuts and seeds</p>\r\n\r\n<p>sunflower, rapeseed and olive oil</p>\r\n\r\n<p>vegetable oils</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Foods to avoid!</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Avoid foods containing saturated fats or eat them only on rare occasions.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>These foods include:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>fatty cuts of meat and meat products, such as sausages and pies</p>\r\n\r\n<p>butter and lard</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Foods to limit!</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="" style="margin:0;" src="images/riskfactors/cholesterol/img2.png" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>cream, soured cream, cr&egrave;me fraiche and ice cream</p>\r\n\r\n<p>cheese, particularly hard cheese</p>\r\n\r\n<p>cakes and biscuits</p>\r\n\r\n<p>chocolate</p>\r\n\r\n<p>coconut oil, coconut cream and palm oil</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The average man should have no more than 30 grams of saturated fat a day.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The average woman should have no more than 20 grams of saturated fat a day.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>To get an idea how much saturated fat you are consuming, take a look at the food labels of the foods you are eating.</p>\r\n', '<h1>Cholesterol</h1>\r\n\r\n<h2 class="h-color">Room for improvement</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Your profile tells us that you have high cholesterol. Evidence tells us that a healthy cholesterol level can improve your long term brain health</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>What causes high cholesterol?</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Eating a diet that is high in saturated fats</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Lack of physical exercise</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Smoking</p>\r\n\r\n<p>High alcohol intake</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Liver or kidney disease</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Know your fats!</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Unsaturated fats</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Small amounts of unsaturated fat in your diet can be healthy. This type of fat can help reduce cholesterol levels.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The traditional Mediterranean <a href="infos-riskfactor.html?riskfactor=9">Diet</a> includes plenty of olive oil and only small amounts of animal fat. It is good for your heart and blood circulation (your cardiovascular health).</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="" src="images/riskfactors/cholesterol/img1.png" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Foods high in unsaturated fats include</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>oily fish</p>\r\n\r\n<p>avocados</p>\r\n\r\n<p>nuts and seeds</p>\r\n\r\n<p>sunflower, rapeseed and olive oil</p>\r\n\r\n<p>vegetable oils</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Foods to avoid!</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Avoid foods containing saturated fats or eat them only on rare occasions.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>These foods include:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>fatty cuts of meat and meat products, such as sausages and pies</p>\r\n\r\n<p>butter and lard</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Foods to limit!</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="" style="margin:0;" src="images/riskfactors/cholesterol/img2.png" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>cream, soured cream, cr&egrave;me fraiche and ice cream</p>\r\n\r\n<p>cheese, particularly hard cheese</p>\r\n\r\n<p>cakes and biscuits</p>\r\n\r\n<p>chocolate</p>\r\n\r\n<p>coconut oil, coconut cream and palm oil</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The average man should have no more than 30 grams of saturated fat a day.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The average woman should have no more than 20 grams of saturated fat a day.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>To get an idea how much saturated fat you are consuming, take a look at the food labels of the foods you are eating.</p>\r\n', '<h3>Further Supports:</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>NHS information on high cholesterol:</p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href="http://www.nhs.uk/conditions/cholesterol/Pages/Introduction.aspx">http://www.nhs.uk/conditions/cholesterol/Pages/Introduction.aspx</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>British heart foundation on high cholesterol:</p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href="http://www.bhf.org.uk/heart-health/conditions/high-cholesterol.aspx">http://www.bhf.org.uk/heart-health/conditions/high-cholesterol.aspx</a></p>'),
	(11, 'en', 'Heart Disease', 'images/libra/heart_disease_amber.png', '<h1>Heart Disease</h1>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="" src="images/riskfactors/heart/heart1.png" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Your profile tells us that you do not suffer from heart disease.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Keeping your heart healthy has other health benefits. For example, it can help protect your brain health.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>How can I prevent heart disease?</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Maintain a healthy weight</li>\r\n	<li>Be physically active, always consult your GP before making any changes to your diet or exercise habits (click <a href="infos-riskfactor.html?riskfactor=4">here</a>)</li>\r\n	<li>Eat a healthy, balanced diet (click <a href="infos-riskfactor.html?riskfactor=9">here</a>)</li>\r\n	<li>Quit smoking (click <a href="infos-riskfactor.html?riskfactor=5">here</a>)</li>\r\n	<li>Reduce stress (click <a href="infos-riskfactor.html?riskfactor=2">here</a>)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="" src="images/riskfactors/heart/heart2.png" /></p>', '<h1>Heart Disease</h1>\r\n\r\n<h2 class="h-color">Remember to manage!</h2>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="" src="images/riskfactors/heart/heart1.png" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Your profile tells us that you suffer from heart disease.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Besides taking medication, you can manage your condition through diet and exercise</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Keeping your heart healthy has other health benefits. For example, it can help protect your brain health.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>How can I prevent heart disease?</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Maintain a healthy weight</li>\r\n	<li>Be physically active, always consult your GP before making any changes to your diet or exercise habits (click <a href="infos-riskfactor.html?riskfactor=4">here</a>)</li>\r\n	<li>Eat a healthy, balanced diet (click <a href="infos-riskfactor.html?riskfactor=9">here</a>)</li>\r\n	<li>Quit smoking (click <a href="infos-riskfactor.html?riskfactor=5">here</a>)</li>\r\n	<li>Reduce stress (click <a href="infos-riskfactor.html?riskfactor=2">here</a>)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="" src="images/riskfactors/heart/heart2.png" /></p>', '<h3>Further Supports:</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Provides information, advice and support on diet and exercise to help you get your cholesterol down to a healthy level</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a href="http://www.irishheart.ie">www.irishheart.ie</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n'),
	(11, 'fr', 'Problmes cardiaques', 'images/libra/heart_disease_amber.png', '<h1>Probl&egrave;mes cardiaques</h1>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="" src="images/riskfactors/heart/heart1.png" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Votre profil nous informe que vous &nbsp;ne souffrez pas de probl&egrave;mes cardiaques.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>En dehors de la prise d&rsquo;un traitement, vous pouvez vous prendre en charge en ayant une alimentation saine et &eacute;quilibr&eacute;e et en faisant de l&rsquo;exercice physique.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Maintenir votre c&oelig;ur en forme a bien d&rsquo;autres avantages pour votre sant&eacute;&nbsp;: cela peut pr&eacute;server la bonne sant&eacute; de votre cerveau par exemple.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Comment puis-je pr&eacute;venir les probl&egrave;mes cardiaques&nbsp;?</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>en gardant un poids normal</li>\r\n	<li>en &eacute;tant physiquement actif, mais toujours en consultant son m&eacute;decin traitant si l&rsquo;on souhaite apporter des changements &agrave; son r&eacute;gime alimentaire ou &agrave; ses habitudes sportives (cliquez <a href="infos-riskfactor.html?riskfactor=4">ici</a>)</li>\r\n	<li>en mangeant de mani&egrave;re saine et &eacute;quilibr&eacute;e (cliquez <a href="infos-riskfactor.html?riskfactor=9">ici</a>)</li>\r\n	<li>en arr&ecirc;tant de fumer (cliquez <a href="infos-riskfactor.html?riskfactor=5">ici</a>)</li>\r\n	<li>en r&eacute;duisant le stress (cliquez<a href="infos-riskfactor.html?riskfactor=2"> ici</a>)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="" src="images/riskfactors/heart/heart2.png" /></p>', '<h1>Probl&egrave;mes cardiaques</h1>\r\n\r\n<h2>Pensez &agrave; les surveiller&nbsp;!</h2>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="" src="images/riskfactors/heart/heart1.png" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Votre profil nous informe que vous souffrez de probl&egrave;mes cardiaques.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>En dehors de la prise d&rsquo;un traitement, vous pouvez vous prendre en charge en ayant une alimentation saine et &eacute;quilibr&eacute;e et en faisant de l&rsquo;exercice physique.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Maintenir votre c&oelig;ur en forme a bien d&rsquo;autres avantages pour votre sant&eacute;&nbsp;: cela peut pr&eacute;server la bonne sant&eacute; de votre cerveau par exemple.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Comment puis-je pr&eacute;venir les probl&egrave;mes cardiaques&nbsp;?</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>en gardant un poids normal</li>\r\n	<li>en &eacute;tant physiquement actif, mais toujours en consultant son m&eacute;decin traitant si l&rsquo;on souhaite apporter des changements &agrave; son r&eacute;gime alimentaire ou &agrave; ses habitudes sportives (cliquez <a href="infos-riskfactor.html?riskfactor=4">ici</a>)</li>\r\n	<li>en mangeant de mani&egrave;re saine et &eacute;quilibr&eacute;e (cliquez <a href="infos-riskfactor.html?riskfactor=9">ici</a>)</li>\r\n	<li>en arr&ecirc;tant de fumer (cliquez <a href="infos-riskfactor.html?riskfactor=5">ici</a>)</li>\r\n	<li>en r&eacute;duisant le stress (cliquez<a href="infos-riskfactor.html?riskfactor=2"> ici</a>)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="" src="images/riskfactors/heart/heart2.png" /></p>', ' '),
	(11, 'sc', 'Heart Disease', 'images/libra/heart_disease_amber.png', '<h1>Heart Disease</h1>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="" src="images/riskfactors/heart/heart1.png" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Your profile tells us that you do not suffer from heart disease.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Keeping your heart healthy has other health benefits. For example, it can help protect your brain health.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>How can I prevent heart disease?</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Maintain a healthy weight</li>\r\n	<li>Be physically active, always consult your GP before making any changes to your diet or exercise habits (click <a href="infos-riskfactor.html?riskfactor=4">here</a>)</li>\r\n	<li>Eat a healthy, balanced diet (click <a href="infos-riskfactor.html?riskfactor=9">here</a>)</li>\r\n	<li>Quit smoking (click <a href="infos-riskfactor.html?riskfactor=5">here</a>)</li>\r\n	<li>Reduce stress (click <a href="infos-riskfactor.html?riskfactor=2">here</a>)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="" src="images/riskfactors/heart/heart2.png" /></p>', '<h1>Heart Disease</h1>\r\n\r\n<h2 class="h-color">Remember to manage!</h2>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="" src="images/riskfactors/heart/heart1.png" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Your profile tells us that you suffer from heart disease.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Besides taking medication, you can manage your condition through diet and exercise</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Keeping your heart healthy has other health benefits. For example, it can help protect your brain health.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>How can I prevent heart disease?</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Maintain a healthy weight</li>\r\n	<li>Be physically active, always consult your GP before making any changes to your diet or exercise habits (click <a href="infos-riskfactor.html?riskfactor=4">here</a>)</li>\r\n	<li>Eat a healthy, balanced diet (click <a href="infos-riskfactor.html?riskfactor=9">here</a>)</li>\r\n	<li>Quit smoking (click <a href="infos-riskfactor.html?riskfactor=5">here</a>)</li>\r\n	<li>Reduce stress (click <a href="infos-riskfactor.html?riskfactor=2">here</a>)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="" src="images/riskfactors/heart/heart2.png" /></p>', '<h3>Further Supports:</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>NHS information on coronary heart disease:</p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href="http://www.nhs.uk/Conditions/Coronary-heart-disease/Pages/Treatment.aspx">http://www.nhs.uk/Conditions/Coronary-heart-disease/Pages/Treatment.aspx</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>British Heart Foundation information on coronary heart disease:</p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href="https://www.bhf.org.uk/heart-health/conditions/coronary-heart-disease.aspx">https://www.bhf.org.uk/heart-health/conditions/coronary-heart-disease.aspx</a></p>'),
	(12, 'en', 'Chronic Kidney Disease', 'images/libra/kidney_disease_amber.png', '<h1>Chronic Kidney Disease</h1>\r\n\r\n<h2 class="h-color">Keep this up!</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Your profile tells us that you do not have Chronic Kidney Disease. In many cases Kidney disease cannot be prevented but there are steps you can take to reduce your risk of developing it.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Below you will find information on further supports</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Evidence tells us that there is an increased risk of dementia in those with chronic kidney disease (CKD).</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Chronic Kidney Disease describes the gradual loss of kidney function. Your kidney filters wastes and excess fluids from your blood, which are then excreted in your urine</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Some causes of CKD are:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>high blood pressure</li>\r\n	<li>Type 1 or 2 Diabetes</li>\r\n	<li>Recurrent kidney infection</li>\r\n	<li>Too much potassium can build up when the kidneys are no longer functioning well</li>\r\n	<li>Potassium if found in many foods.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>What Can I do?</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Stick to the recommended alcohol consumption limits (See our alcohol page <a href="infos-riskfactor.html?riskfactor=6">here</a>)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Eat a healthy balanced diet that includes plenty of fresh fruit and vegetable and fish (see our diet page <a href="infos-riskfactor.html?riskfactor=9">here</a>)</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="" src="images/riskfactors/diabetes/img2.png" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Take regular exercise (see our exercise page <a href="infos-riskfactor.html?riskfactor=4">here</a>)</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="" src="images/riskfactors/diabetes/img3.png" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Quit smoking (see our smoking page <a href="infos-riskfactor.html?riskfactor=5">here</a>)</p>', '<h1>Chronic Kidney Disease</h1>\r\n\r\n<h2 class="h-color">Remember to manage well</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Your profile tells us that you have Chronic Kidney Disease. Your doctor will be assisting you in managing this. In many cases Kidney disease cannot be prevented but there are steps you can take to reduce your risk of developing it.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Below you will find information on further supports</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Evidence tells us that there is an increased risk of dementia in those with chronic kidney disease (CKD).</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Chronic Kidney Disease describes the gradual loss of kidney function. Your kidney filters wastes and excess fluids from your blood, which are then excreted in your urine</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Some causes of CKD are:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>high blood pressure</li>\r\n	<li>Type 1 or 2 Diabetes</li>\r\n	<li>Recurrent kidney infection</li>\r\n	<li>Too much potassium can build up when the kidneys are no longer functioning well</li>\r\n	<li>Potassium if found in many foods.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>What Can I do?</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Stick to the recommended alcohol consumption limits (See our alcohol page <a href="infos-riskfactor.html?riskfactor=6">here</a>)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Eat a healthy balanced diet that includes plenty of fresh fruit and vegetable and fish (see our diet page <a href="infos-riskfactor.html?riskfactor=9">here</a>)</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="" src="images/riskfactors/diabetes/img2.png" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Take regular exercise (see our exercise page <a href="infos-riskfactor.html?riskfactor=4">here</a>)</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="" src="images/riskfactors/diabetes/img3.png" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Quit smoking (see our smoking page <a href="infos-riskfactor.html?riskfactor=5">here</a>)</p>', '<h3>Further Supports:</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>This site offers, facts, information, education and diet advice for those with Chronic Kidney Disease</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a href="http://www.ika.ie">www.ika.ie</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n'),
	(12, 'fr', 'Insuffisance rnale chronique', 'images/libra/kidney_disease_amber.png', '<h1>Insuffisance r&eacute;nale chronique</h1>\r\n\r\n<h2>Continuez comme &ccedil;a&nbsp;!&nbsp;</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>YoVotre profil nous informe que vous ne souffrez pas d&rsquo;insuffisance r&eacute;nale chronique. Dans de nombreux cas l&rsquo;insuffisance r&eacute;nale ne peut pas &ecirc;tre anticip&eacute;e mais il existe des marches &agrave; suivre pour r&eacute;duire les risques d&rsquo;en &ecirc;tre atteint.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Vous trouverez ci-dessous les informations pour un soutien plus pouss&eacute;.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Des recherches ont montr&eacute; que le risque de d&eacute;mence est plus &eacute;lev&eacute; chez les personnes souffrant d&rsquo;insuffisance r&eacute;nale chronique.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>L&rsquo;insuffisance r&eacute;nale chronique est la perte progressive de la fonction r&eacute;nale. Vos reins filtrent les d&eacute;chets organiques et les exc&eacute;dents de fluides du corps, qui sont &eacute;vacu&eacute;s dans les urines.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Certaines causes de l&rsquo;insuffisance r&eacute;nale chronique sont&nbsp;:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>l&rsquo;hypertension art&eacute;rielle</li>\r\n	<li>les diab&egrave;tes de type 1 et 2</li>\r\n	<li>les infections r&eacute;nales &agrave; r&eacute;p&eacute;tition</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;Quand les reins de fonctionnent plus bien, la potassium peut s&rsquo;accumuler en trop grande quantit&eacute;. On trouve du potassium dans de nombreux aliments.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Que puis-je faire&nbsp;?</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Il faut vous tenir strictement aux limites recommand&eacute;es en mati&egrave;re de consommation d&rsquo;alcool.&nbsp;(consultez notre page sur l&rsquo;alcool <a href="infos-riskfactor.html?riskfactor=6">ici</a>)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Suivre un r&eacute;gime alimentaire sain et &eacute;quilibr&eacute; qui inclut de nombreux fruits et l&eacute;gumes frais ainsi que du poisson (consultez notre page sur le r&eacute;gime alimentaire<a href="infos-riskfactor.html?riskfactor=9"> ici</a>)</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="" src="images/riskfactors/diabetes/img2.png" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Pratiquer un sport r&eacute;guli&egrave;rement (consultez notre page sur l&rsquo;exercice physique <a href="infos-riskfactor.html?riskfactor=4">ici</a>)</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="" src="images/riskfactors/diabetes/img3.png" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Arr&ecirc;ter de fumer (consultez notre page sur la cigarette <a href="infos-riskfactor.html?riskfactor=5">ici</a>)</p>', '<h1>Insuffisance r&eacute;nale chronique</h1>\r\n\r\n<h2 class="h-color">Pensez &agrave; la surveiller</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Votre profil nous informe que vous souffrez d&rsquo;une insuffisance r&eacute;nale chronique. Votre m&eacute;decin vous aidera &agrave; la prendre en charge. Dans de nombreux cas l&rsquo;insuffisance r&eacute;nale ne peut pas &ecirc;tre anticip&eacute;e mais il existe des marches &agrave; suivre pour r&eacute;duire les risques d&rsquo;en &ecirc;tre atteint.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Vous trouverez ci-dessous les informations pour un soutien plus pouss&eacute;.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Des recherches ont montr&eacute; que le risque de d&eacute;mence est plus &eacute;lev&eacute; chez les personnes souffrant d&rsquo;insuffisance r&eacute;nale chronique.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>L&rsquo;insuffisance r&eacute;nale chronique est la perte progressive de la fonction r&eacute;nale. Vos reins filtrent les d&eacute;chets organiques et les exc&eacute;dents de fluides du corps, qui sont &eacute;vacu&eacute;s dans les urines.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Certaines causes de l&rsquo;insuffisance r&eacute;nale chronique sont&nbsp;:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>l&rsquo;hypertension art&eacute;rielle</li>\r\n	<li>les diab&egrave;tes de type 1 et 2</li>\r\n	<li>les infections r&eacute;nales &agrave; r&eacute;p&eacute;tition</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;Quand les reins de fonctionnent plus bien, la potassium peut s&rsquo;accumuler en trop grande quantit&eacute;. On trouve du potassium dans de nombreux aliments.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Que puis-je faire&nbsp;?</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Il faut vous tenir strictement aux limites recommand&eacute;es en mati&egrave;re de consommation d&rsquo;alcool.&nbsp;(consultez notre page sur l&rsquo;alcool <a href="infos-riskfactor.html?riskfactor=6">ici</a>)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Suivre un r&eacute;gime alimentaire sain et &eacute;quilibr&eacute; qui inclut de nombreux fruits et l&eacute;gumes frais ainsi que du poisson (consultez notre page sur le r&eacute;gime alimentaire<a href="infos-riskfactor.html?riskfactor=9"> ici</a>)</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="" src="images/riskfactors/diabetes/img2.png" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Pratiquer un sport r&eacute;guli&egrave;rement (consultez notre page sur l&rsquo;exercice physique <a href="infos-riskfactor.html?riskfactor=4">ici</a>)</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="" src="images/riskfactors/diabetes/img3.png" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Arr&ecirc;ter de fumer (consultez notre page sur la cigarette <a href="infos-riskfactor.html?riskfactor=5">ici</a>)</p>', ' '),
